WEBVTT

00:00:06.419 --> 00:00:08.421
[waves crashing]

00:00:33.655 --> 00:00:35.949
[engine revving]

00:00:49.671 --> 00:00:52.006
[knocking on door]

00:00:55.218 --> 00:00:57.095
Hey, Sonny. Five minutes.

00:01:02.392 --> 00:01:04.894
["Whole Lotta Love" playing]

00:01:13.278 --> 00:01:14.779
♪ You need coolin' ♪

00:01:14.863 --> 00:01:16.281
[grunts]

00:01:16.364 --> 00:01:17.907
♪ Baby, I'm not foolin' ♪

00:01:18.783 --> 00:01:23.454
♪ I'm gonna send ya
Back to schoolin' ♪

00:01:24.998 --> 00:01:29.878
♪ Way down inside
Honey, you need it ♪

00:01:30.587 --> 00:01:35.466
♪ I'm gonna give you my love
I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:01:35.550 --> 00:01:37.635
[people chattering]

00:01:37.719 --> 00:01:41.472
♪ Want a whole lotta love
Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:01:42.432 --> 00:01:46.978
Sonny! Hey. BMW guys are over there
bitching about brake trouble.

00:01:47.061 --> 00:01:48.438
Thanks, Molly. You're a superstar.

00:01:48.521 --> 00:01:49.689
I'll see you out there.

00:01:51.107 --> 00:01:55.695
♪ All the good times
Baby, baby, I've been yearning ♪

00:01:57.071 --> 00:02:01.034
♪ Way, way down inside
Honey, you need it ♪

00:02:02.118 --> 00:02:04.996
♪ I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:02:05.079 --> 00:02:07.248
♪ I'm gonna give you my love ♪

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:11.461
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:02:11.544 --> 00:02:13.295
Turn my back for one minute.

00:02:13.838 --> 00:02:15.423
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:02:16.674 --> 00:02:18.801
It's all gone to shit, Sonny.

00:02:18.885 --> 00:02:20.178
Pat had to ease off.

00:02:20.261 --> 00:02:21.721
We've dropped down to seventh.

00:02:22.222 --> 00:02:26.726
If you can just hold position overnight,
hopeful sunrise catches us a break.

00:02:31.397 --> 00:02:35.318
Sonny, watch that high-speed balance.
High-speed balance.

00:02:37.904 --> 00:02:39.781
[drills whirring]

00:02:39.864 --> 00:02:41.032
How's the gearbox?

00:02:41.115 --> 00:02:42.367
It's holding up, but go easy.

00:02:43.201 --> 00:02:44.827
[breathing deeply]

00:02:46.538 --> 00:02:48.831
[breathing heavily]

00:03:02.178 --> 00:03:05.390
[commentator] The crowds may
have gone home, but the racing continues.

00:03:05.473 --> 00:03:08.935
Sonny Hayes back in the Porsche
for Peak Geico Chip Hart Racing,

00:03:09.018 --> 00:03:10.562
the midnight shift.

00:03:10.645 --> 00:03:12.063
We all know Hayes

00:03:12.146 --> 00:03:13.273
likes to light up the night,

00:03:13.356 --> 00:03:17.360
but with the BMW at the head of this pack,
he's got a massive job ahead of him.

00:03:29.706 --> 00:03:32.584
Right out of the gate,
Hayes threads the needle into turn three,

00:03:32.667 --> 00:03:33.710
moving up to fourth place.

00:03:33.793 --> 00:03:35.920
Sonny, wanna maybe pass on the straights?

00:03:36.004 --> 00:03:37.255
Just let me drive, will ya?

00:03:39.591 --> 00:03:40.800
[song continues]

00:03:40.884 --> 00:03:43.469
[commentator] Look out.
Engine trouble for the number 12.

00:03:46.139 --> 00:03:48.224
That moves Hayes up another spot.

00:03:58.651 --> 00:04:03.656
♪ You've been coolin'
Baby, I've been droolin' ♪

00:04:04.782 --> 00:04:06.743
Sweet baby Jesus. We got ten more hours.

00:04:07.327 --> 00:04:09.204
Just let Sonny do his thing.

00:04:09.287 --> 00:04:11.748
And if these first few laps
are any indication,

00:04:11.831 --> 00:04:15.293
it appears as though Sonny Hayes
may have left his brake pedal at home.

00:04:15.376 --> 00:04:17.962
♪ I'm gonna give you
Every inch of my love ♪

00:04:18.046 --> 00:04:20.297
Hayes sets his sights on the BMW.

00:04:20.380 --> 00:04:22.966
♪ Yeah, all right, let's go ♪

00:04:23.051 --> 00:04:24.636
-[grunts]
-[commentator] And he attacks.

00:04:24.719 --> 00:04:28.431
♪ Want a whole lotta love
Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:04:28.515 --> 00:04:30.642
[commentator]
Here comes Hayes on the outside.

00:04:30.725 --> 00:04:31.893
Come on, Sonny.

00:04:31.976 --> 00:04:33.895
♪ Want a whole lotta love ♪

00:04:36.314 --> 00:04:40.318
♪ Way down inside ♪

00:04:43.821 --> 00:04:45.156
[pants]

00:04:45.240 --> 00:04:51.412
♪ Love ♪

00:04:56.709 --> 00:05:00.505
♪ My, my, my, my
My, my, my, my ♪

00:05:00.588 --> 00:05:03.716
[commentator] The BMW late on the brakes.
He's in the grass.

00:05:08.429 --> 00:05:09.597
Can Hayes hang on?

00:05:11.182 --> 00:05:12.183
And he does.

00:05:12.267 --> 00:05:13.601
Goddamn!

00:05:14.269 --> 00:05:16.229
See that? That's how you race, boys.

00:05:16.312 --> 00:05:19.274
When you get back in that car,
you need to do the same goddamn thing.

00:05:19.357 --> 00:05:23.903
♪ Hey, oh, ooh ♪

00:05:23.987 --> 00:05:27.365
[commentator] Sonny Hayes brings it
into pit lane after an epic third stint

00:05:27.448 --> 00:05:29.742
that puts Chip Hart Racing out in front.

00:05:30.243 --> 00:05:33.037
Now, it's up to Cale Kelso
to hang on to that lead.

00:05:33.121 --> 00:05:34.789
[Kelso] Thanks for the head start, Chief.

00:05:38.084 --> 00:05:40.628
Hey. Lose that lead, I'll kill ya.

00:05:43.298 --> 00:05:48.344
♪ Shake for me, girl
I wanna be your backdoor man ♪

00:05:48.428 --> 00:05:49.596
[BMW driver] Hayes!

00:05:50.180 --> 00:05:51.556
Hey, dirt bag!

00:05:53.433 --> 00:05:55.977
-Gonna run me off the track, Hayes?
-[crew member] It's not worth it.

00:05:56.060 --> 00:05:59.731
You think I don't know where to find you?
Screw you!

00:06:01.232 --> 00:06:02.400
Let go of me!

00:06:03.401 --> 00:06:04.819
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

00:06:04.903 --> 00:06:06.321
Hey. Attaboy, Sonny.

00:06:07.363 --> 00:06:09.532
Thanks. Don't wake me if we lose.

00:06:10.074 --> 00:06:13.286
[crowd cheering]

00:06:13.953 --> 00:06:15.622
[laughs]

00:06:17.582 --> 00:06:19.292
[cheers]

00:06:19.375 --> 00:06:21.085
♪ Keep it coolin', baby ♪

00:06:21.169 --> 00:06:22.712
[song fades]

00:06:24.506 --> 00:06:27.300
Sonny Hayes,
I believe you forgot something.

00:06:28.259 --> 00:06:29.385
Bag's full, Chip.

00:06:30.261 --> 00:06:31.262
Seriously?

00:06:31.930 --> 00:06:34.557
Your first win at Daytona.
Don't you even want to touch it?

00:06:34.641 --> 00:06:35.642
-Ooh, bad luck.
-Come on.

00:06:35.725 --> 00:06:37.644
-Just touch it.
-[laughing] No. Hey.

00:06:38.728 --> 00:06:40.813
I will take that bonus check though.

00:06:42.106 --> 00:06:46.277
Sonny. Sonny! Just hear me out.

00:06:47.111 --> 00:06:48.488
Look, I wanna bring you on board.

00:06:48.571 --> 00:06:49.989
-[laughs]
-You're CHR family now.

00:06:50.073 --> 00:06:51.866
Right here, next year, let's run it back.

00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:53.826
We did it, man. Deal's a deal.

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:56.079
I-I know what a deal is.

00:06:57.622 --> 00:06:59.374
So that's it? One and done?

00:06:59.457 --> 00:07:02.043
I appreciate the seat, Chip. I really do.

00:07:02.126 --> 00:07:03.628
What kind of way is that to race?

00:07:04.128 --> 00:07:06.047
You just spend your whole life
starting over, man.

00:07:06.130 --> 00:07:07.131
You take care.

00:07:08.299 --> 00:07:10.218
-[engine starts]
-I'll see you down the road.

00:07:17.976 --> 00:07:20.103
Hey! Don't you want the watch?

00:07:20.186 --> 00:07:21.271
[Sonny] Got one!

00:07:21.354 --> 00:07:22.939
["Round and Round" playing on radio]

00:07:23.022 --> 00:07:24.774
[radio presenter 1]
WHOG, Ormond-by-the-Sea.

00:07:24.858 --> 00:07:26.193
[radio presenter 2]
Proud to be locally owned.

00:07:26.276 --> 00:07:27.735
A Southern Stone station.

00:07:27.819 --> 00:07:29.153
The world's most famous rock…

00:07:29.237 --> 00:07:32.448
[radio presenter 1] …from the world's
most famous beach, we are…

00:07:32.532 --> 00:07:34.242
[radio presenter 2]
…Daytona's rock station…

00:07:34.325 --> 00:07:36.205
[radio presenter 1]
…ninety-five seven, the Hog.

00:07:37.245 --> 00:07:40.874
♪ Out on the streets
That's where we'll meet ♪

00:07:40.957 --> 00:07:44.878
♪ You make the night
I always cross the line ♪

00:07:44.961 --> 00:07:48.256
♪ Tightened our belts
Abused ourselves ♪

00:07:48.339 --> 00:07:49.925
♪ Get in our way
We'll put you on your shelf ♪

00:07:50.008 --> 00:07:51.217
[timer buzzes]

00:07:52.135 --> 00:07:55.305
Sorry, can I use your phone
for a second, please?

00:07:55.388 --> 00:07:56.556
It's not working.

00:07:56.639 --> 00:07:58.474
Um, no.

00:08:01.311 --> 00:08:04.564
You know, you remind me of this friend
I used to have.

00:08:04.647 --> 00:08:05.648
Which friend?

00:08:06.149 --> 00:08:07.400
Friend who dressed better.

00:08:08.651 --> 00:08:10.028
This is a Gucci suit.

00:08:10.111 --> 00:08:11.237
So's this.

00:08:11.321 --> 00:08:13.239
Huh. What did your friend do?

00:08:13.323 --> 00:08:14.324
Drove cars.

00:08:14.407 --> 00:08:16.159
-Was he fast?
-Wasn't slow.

00:08:16.242 --> 00:08:19.287
-Did he win?
-[inhales sharply] Yeah, he did.

00:08:21.497 --> 00:08:23.833
-Come here, you son of a bitch.
-[laughs]

00:08:23.917 --> 00:08:24.918
Oh, God.

00:08:25.001 --> 00:08:26.711
[friend] Are you thinking Baja?

00:08:26.794 --> 00:08:28.880
[Sonny] Yeah. New day, new challenge.

00:08:28.963 --> 00:08:31.258
That's exactly what I said to myself
when I bought Apex GP.

00:08:31.341 --> 00:08:33.968
-["The Stroke" playing on radio]
-[groans]

00:08:34.052 --> 00:08:35.512
How deep in the hole are you?

00:08:36.679 --> 00:08:39.057
I'll tell you,
but you have to promise not to laugh.

00:08:39.890 --> 00:08:40.933
Shoot.

00:08:42.684 --> 00:08:44.145
350…

00:08:45.647 --> 00:08:47.190
Million.

00:08:49.609 --> 00:08:50.693
Don't laugh.

00:08:52.153 --> 00:08:53.321
Impressive.

00:08:54.531 --> 00:08:55.740
Well, been fun?

00:08:55.823 --> 00:08:57.992
Oh, yeah. Absolutely.

00:08:58.076 --> 00:08:59.244
What's the problem then?

00:08:59.327 --> 00:09:02.664
Problem is two seasons and a half,
zero points.

00:09:02.747 --> 00:09:04.874
My best driver left for another team.

00:09:04.958 --> 00:09:07.210
He said the car was a shitbox.

00:09:07.293 --> 00:09:08.294
[laughs]

00:09:08.378 --> 00:09:10.046
The team is in last place.

00:09:10.129 --> 00:09:11.673
My number two's a rookie.

00:09:12.173 --> 00:09:13.633
And the season's half over.

00:09:13.716 --> 00:09:15.260
-How many races left?
-Nine.

00:09:15.760 --> 00:09:17.720
And if we don't turn it around,
I lose the team.

00:09:17.804 --> 00:09:19.305
-What?
-Mmm.

00:09:19.389 --> 00:09:20.515
But you own the team.

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:25.228
No race wins in your first three seasons,
the board can force a sale.

00:09:26.729 --> 00:09:28.648
Man, sounds like you need a new board.

00:09:30.275 --> 00:09:31.484
I need a new driver.

00:09:36.906 --> 00:09:39.284
[laughs]

00:09:40.243 --> 00:09:41.661
[Sonny] You got F2. You got F3.

00:09:41.744 --> 00:09:44.247
You got an entire assembly line of kids
raised on the simulator.

00:09:44.330 --> 00:09:47.458
No, I don't have time for some kid
to learn how to come in tenth. I don't.

00:09:47.542 --> 00:09:50.211
Well, you don't just walk off the street
and pilot a rocket.

00:09:50.295 --> 00:09:52.881
Yes, you can if you've done it before.
That's the whole point.

00:09:52.964 --> 00:09:57.010
Louis Chiron was 57 years old
when he won the Monaco Grand Prix.

00:09:57.093 --> 00:09:59.429
-Louis who?
-Philippe Étancelin, 56 years old.

00:09:59.512 --> 00:10:00.806
You just Googled these names, didn't you?

00:10:00.889 --> 00:10:04.517
Some people look at Sonny Hayes,
they see a guy who lives in a van,

00:10:04.601 --> 00:10:06.644
a gambling junkie who missed his shot.

00:10:06.728 --> 00:10:08.855
Wow, Ruben, you are really selling this.

00:10:08.938 --> 00:10:11.065
But I see a guy who makes teams better.

00:10:11.149 --> 00:10:13.151
-I see experience. I see know-how.
-Mmm.

00:10:13.234 --> 00:10:14.361
[laughs] You're off your meds.

00:10:14.444 --> 00:10:17.989
My rookie's a phenomenal talent.
Phenomenal. But he's young.

00:10:18.489 --> 00:10:19.949
You know what he lacks? Maturity.

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:22.243
You plus him?

00:10:22.327 --> 00:10:24.495
Boom. I got a team.

00:10:24.579 --> 00:10:26.581
[Sonny]
All right. Let's say I'm the next Louis…

00:10:26.664 --> 00:10:28.499
-Chiron. Mm-hmm.
-Him.

00:10:29.501 --> 00:10:32.086
The problem is it's not just the driver,
it's the car.

00:10:32.837 --> 00:10:34.589
I've followed your season, Ruben.

00:10:34.672 --> 00:10:36.007
"Shitbox" is being kind.

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:37.300
I knew you were watching.

00:10:37.383 --> 00:10:40.136
What if I told you
we get an upgrade package this weekend?

00:10:40.220 --> 00:10:42.013
-Six months in development...
-Ruben…

00:10:42.096 --> 00:10:43.223
No, no, no. Wait.

00:10:43.306 --> 00:10:47.435
I just need one of my cars
across the finish line first. One.

00:10:48.019 --> 00:10:49.979
I love ya. I'm not going back.

00:10:51.356 --> 00:10:52.482
[sighs]

00:10:54.108 --> 00:10:55.109
Okay.

00:10:58.613 --> 00:11:00.323
What would he want you to do?

00:11:00.406 --> 00:11:02.325
[chuckles]

00:11:02.951 --> 00:11:03.952
[Sonny] Join a boy band?

00:11:04.035 --> 00:11:05.578
Seriously. Come on.

00:11:07.747 --> 00:11:09.791
Seriously, I'd ask him
what he's smiling about.

00:11:09.874 --> 00:11:10.875
Come on.

00:11:11.876 --> 00:11:14.087
He's smiling at the possibility.

00:11:16.005 --> 00:11:17.507
We both know how that ended.

00:11:19.342 --> 00:11:20.343
Yep.

00:11:21.427 --> 00:11:22.428
Okay.

00:11:23.096 --> 00:11:26.558
-This is a first-class ticket to London.
-Oh, my God.

00:11:26.641 --> 00:11:27.851
First class.

00:11:27.934 --> 00:11:31.437
I'm offering you
an open seat in Formula 1.

00:11:32.397 --> 00:11:35.066
The only place you could say for one day,

00:11:35.149 --> 00:11:40.405
if you win,
you are the absolute best in the world.

00:11:50.456 --> 00:11:52.292
-Hey, Ruben.
-Mmm.

00:11:52.834 --> 00:11:54.794
-Ever seen a miracle?
-Not yet.

00:11:55.420 --> 00:11:56.504
Me neither.

00:11:57.547 --> 00:11:58.715
Good to see you, amigo.

00:12:00.925 --> 00:12:03.011
-All right, sweetie, here you go.
-Thank you.

00:12:03.094 --> 00:12:05.305
-Mm-hmm.
-Hey, let me ask you something.

00:12:07.557 --> 00:12:12.145
Close friend of yours made you an offer
that was 100%, positively

00:12:12.228 --> 00:12:13.479
too good to be true.

00:12:14.439 --> 00:12:15.440
What do you do?

00:12:15.523 --> 00:12:18.151
[sighs] Well, how much are we talking?

00:12:18.234 --> 00:12:19.611
Not about the money.

00:12:21.196 --> 00:12:22.697
So what is it about?

00:12:23.823 --> 00:12:24.908
Hmm.

00:12:36.169 --> 00:12:37.629
[engine revving]

00:12:55.480 --> 00:12:58.066
[driving synth music playing]

00:13:06.282 --> 00:13:09.160
[crew member] Tire temps look good.
Eighty-five front, 75 rear.

00:13:09.244 --> 00:13:11.538
-You are good to push.
-[driver] Copy.

00:13:20.463 --> 00:13:22.299
[crew member] Battery is full.
You're good for strat two.

00:13:22.382 --> 00:13:23.383
[driver] Going for a lap.

00:13:41.150 --> 00:13:43.361
Purple sector one. Best one yet.

00:13:44.028 --> 00:13:45.196
[driver] Car feels good.

00:14:20.106 --> 00:14:21.691
[tires squeal]

00:14:21.774 --> 00:14:22.817
Damn!

00:14:26.905 --> 00:14:28.907
Locked it up. Flat spot, front left.

00:14:34.662 --> 00:14:36.289
[sighs]

00:14:37.248 --> 00:14:38.333
Bring him in.

00:14:38.416 --> 00:14:39.792
Go to strat one.

00:14:39.876 --> 00:14:41.628
Uh, box this lap. Box this lap.

00:14:54.265 --> 00:14:56.768
-[groans]
-Let's go find those gremlins.

00:15:15.411 --> 00:15:16.704
[blows]

00:15:19.791 --> 00:15:22.293
[crew chattering]

00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:25.380
[groans]

00:15:32.512 --> 00:15:33.930
[grunts, gasps]

00:15:34.013 --> 00:15:35.265
Sorry, Joshua.

00:15:38.226 --> 00:15:40.311
Jodie, try not to kill our driver.

00:15:47.193 --> 00:15:48.945
What's the verdict? [sniffs]

00:15:49.028 --> 00:15:52.615
[sighs] I don't know what's happening.
I mean, it feels good. I start to push.

00:15:53.116 --> 00:15:55.494
Then it understeers in the slow corners
and oversteers the fast.

00:15:55.577 --> 00:15:57.120
What? On entries or exits?

00:15:57.203 --> 00:15:58.830
Either. Both.

00:15:58.913 --> 00:16:00.206
Oh, great. Yeah.

00:16:00.290 --> 00:16:03.085
There's 10,000 sensors on this thing
and you can't tell me what's going on.

00:16:03.168 --> 00:16:04.961
But I'm not out there, am I?

00:16:05.044 --> 00:16:07.964
So, I-I'm gonna need
your help on this. Please.

00:16:12.510 --> 00:16:15.263
[speaking German]

00:16:16.139 --> 00:16:17.390
[speaking German]

00:16:22.604 --> 00:16:24.522
[child giggles]

00:16:24.606 --> 00:16:27.192
[in English]
150 million dollar jungle gym.

00:16:27.817 --> 00:16:28.818
So cute.

00:16:29.444 --> 00:16:32.363
We should let her drive.
Can't be any worse.

00:16:33.114 --> 00:16:34.782
[child imitating engine]

00:16:35.450 --> 00:16:36.784
Joshua.

00:16:36.868 --> 00:16:39.120
-Hi.
-Lisbeth. PR?

00:16:39.204 --> 00:16:40.872
-Oh, yeah.
-Doesn't matter.

00:16:40.955 --> 00:16:43.583
For the press conference,
we want to steer around tech issues

00:16:43.666 --> 00:16:47.128
and focus on the super strong bond
with your new teammate, Luca Cortez.

00:16:47.212 --> 00:16:48.963
[laughs] Luca?

00:16:49.047 --> 00:16:50.465
Who I've known a week.

00:16:51.007 --> 00:16:53.134
Who when he was third banana
on the left at Red Bull,

00:16:53.218 --> 00:16:55.720
told the press he thought
Joshua Pearce was overrated.

00:16:56.763 --> 00:16:58.181
That Luca Cortez?

00:16:58.264 --> 00:16:59.724
Yes.

00:16:59.807 --> 00:17:02.936
-[chuckles] Can't wait. Yeah.
-All right. Great. Thank you.

00:17:03.019 --> 00:17:04.020
-Yo.
-Yep.

00:17:04.103 --> 00:17:06.314
That's a yes? Yeah? Yes? [groans]

00:17:06.397 --> 00:17:07.398
[Joshua] What's up?

00:17:07.482 --> 00:17:09.108
Yo, you were right, bro.

00:17:09.651 --> 00:17:12.111
Ruben's in big trouble.
He might have to sell the team.

00:17:12.194 --> 00:17:14.030
-[snaps fingers]
-I knew it.

00:17:14.113 --> 00:17:15.282
And what does that mean for me?

00:17:15.365 --> 00:17:17.742
New buyers, they're likely to clean house.

00:17:18.952 --> 00:17:19.953
Listen.

00:17:20.537 --> 00:17:24.624
You need to show these people
who the number one driver really is, man.

00:17:25.250 --> 00:17:26.251
Now.

00:17:27.919 --> 00:17:29.212
Or you're gonna lose your job.

00:17:29.753 --> 00:17:32.423
Yeah. Let that sink in.

00:17:32.507 --> 00:17:34.759
[speaking German]

00:17:35.552 --> 00:17:37.720
-[in English] Hey.
-[parent, speaking German]

00:17:38.930 --> 00:17:40.265
You good?

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:46.855
Okay, let's take
the first half of the season

00:17:46.938 --> 00:17:48.940
and erase it from our minds.

00:17:49.023 --> 00:17:50.024
[crew cheers]

00:17:50.108 --> 00:17:52.318
Someone says,
"Kaspar, what happened this year?"

00:17:52.902 --> 00:17:56.948
I swear on the lives of my children,
I do not freaking know.

00:17:57.031 --> 00:17:58.366
[laughs]

00:17:58.449 --> 00:17:59.701
There's only this car.

00:18:00.285 --> 00:18:03.955
And there is only our future.

00:18:04.038 --> 00:18:06.833
[crew exclaiming] Yes. Our future.

00:18:15.842 --> 00:18:17.427
[Kaspar] Who is that asshole?

00:18:17.510 --> 00:18:18.511
He's with me.

00:18:19.429 --> 00:18:22.223
Your man thought I was maintenance.
Sent me to the back gate.

00:18:22.307 --> 00:18:23.683
[Ruben chuckles]

00:18:24.726 --> 00:18:26.144
Brother, you have never let me down.

00:18:26.227 --> 00:18:28.313
-[chuckles] Well, there's still time.
-[chuckles]

00:18:28.396 --> 00:18:29.981
Apex GP!

00:18:30.064 --> 00:18:32.525
Sonny Hayes.
He raced with me back in the day.

00:18:32.609 --> 00:18:34.360
-Against you, you mean.
-Yeah.

00:18:34.444 --> 00:18:36.905
-Kate McKenna, our technical director.
-Hi.

00:18:36.988 --> 00:18:39.908
-Dodge Dauda, our chief mechanic.
-Hi.

00:18:39.991 --> 00:18:42.160
And Kaspar Smolinski, team principal.

00:18:42.243 --> 00:18:43.786
You may know him by reputation.

00:18:43.870 --> 00:18:46.623
Five-time Constructors champion
with Ferrari.

00:18:47.165 --> 00:18:48.499
Huh.

00:18:49.250 --> 00:18:50.418
As a rear jack man.

00:18:50.502 --> 00:18:52.128
So was my pop. Can't win without 'em.

00:18:52.212 --> 00:18:55.089
-And our talented rookie, Joshua.
-Why has he got a helmet?

00:18:56.174 --> 00:18:58.051
-Uh, safety?
-[chuckles]

00:18:58.134 --> 00:19:00.512
Joshua, your seat is safe. Okay?

00:19:00.595 --> 00:19:02.514
Sonny is here for the audition.

00:19:04.933 --> 00:19:06.351
When was the last time you won a race?

00:19:06.434 --> 00:19:08.061
Sunday. Daytona.

00:19:08.144 --> 00:19:10.063
Oh, I'm sorry. I-I meant Formula 1.

00:19:10.146 --> 00:19:12.398
Oh, I'm sorry. Then same as you.

00:19:12.482 --> 00:19:15.485
-[laughs, exclaims] Wow.
-[chuckles]

00:19:15.568 --> 00:19:18.279
Never thought I'd say this,
has anyone seen Luca Cortez?

00:19:18.363 --> 00:19:20.406
-[chuckles]
-Sidebar bitte, Ruben.

00:19:20.490 --> 00:19:23.451
When I interview with you,
many veteran drivers...

00:19:23.535 --> 00:19:25.119
Yeah, who all turned you down.

00:19:25.203 --> 00:19:26.746
-How many?
-Seven.

00:19:26.829 --> 00:19:28.581
-That's a lot.
-I'm number seven?

00:19:28.665 --> 00:19:30.083
-Mm-hmm.
-You're eight.

00:19:30.166 --> 00:19:31.417
This is a disaster.

00:19:31.501 --> 00:19:32.794
Starting to feel more like a nine.

00:19:32.877 --> 00:19:34.588
Technically, there is one
who I've not heard from yet.

00:19:34.671 --> 00:19:35.797
-[stammers]
-So I am a nine?

00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:37.465
You know how numbers work, right?

00:19:37.549 --> 00:19:40.468
In business,
my most inspired ideas come late.

00:19:40.552 --> 00:19:43.096
Yeah. Best things in life
usually arrive ninth, right?

00:19:43.179 --> 00:19:46.599
With respect, Ruben, I cannot condone
we spend our only test day

00:19:46.683 --> 00:19:48.810
giving your long-lost teammate
an audition.

00:19:48.893 --> 00:19:50.228
Kaspar, you misunderstand.

00:19:50.311 --> 00:19:52.647
We're not auditioning him.
He's auditioning us.

00:19:54.065 --> 00:19:55.358
That's your new driver.

00:19:55.441 --> 00:19:56.526
Good luck.

00:19:59.696 --> 00:20:01.114
New wing, new side pods.

00:20:01.197 --> 00:20:02.615
Any changes to the floor?

00:20:03.783 --> 00:20:06.411
Nothing the eight other drivers
wouldn't have figured out.

00:20:07.287 --> 00:20:09.038
That's why they call me Lucky Number Nine.

00:20:09.122 --> 00:20:11.916
Listen, it's been a while
since you've driven here, mate. Yeah?

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:14.761
The balance on these cars are tricky,
so be careful turn one and nine.

00:20:14.878 --> 00:20:16.238
Wouldn't want to see you get hurt.

00:20:17.505 --> 00:20:18.965
How about we set a reasonable target?

00:20:19.048 --> 00:20:22.635
Give me the same setup as him. If I can't
post a lap time within a second of JP's,

00:20:22.719 --> 00:20:24.387
then I will promptly see myself out

00:20:25.054 --> 00:20:27.015
and you're free to take a shot
at lucky number ten.

00:20:27.098 --> 00:20:28.808
-Ten?
-Ten.

00:20:29.517 --> 00:20:30.518
Ten.

00:20:32.729 --> 00:20:33.813
Who's JP?

00:20:35.148 --> 00:20:36.691
[rock music playing]

00:20:37.817 --> 00:20:40.528
Cross round on Brooklands,
easy on Luffield.

00:20:40.612 --> 00:20:42.780
Up to Woodcote, hard out in Copse.

00:20:42.864 --> 00:20:44.157
And be careful on the curve.

00:20:48.912 --> 00:20:51.873
Default mode, settings one, to two,
back to three.

00:20:52.498 --> 00:20:54.250
Differential one through four.

00:20:54.334 --> 00:20:55.627
DRS.

00:20:59.756 --> 00:21:03.551
♪ I bet you thought
You'd seen the last of me ♪

00:21:03.635 --> 00:21:07.096
♪ I can't change the way I am, you see ♪

00:21:07.180 --> 00:21:09.015
♪ I think it's my responsibility ♪

00:21:09.098 --> 00:21:10.600
[exhales deeply]

00:21:10.683 --> 00:21:14.312
♪ To tell you
I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:14.395 --> 00:21:16.231
[engine starts, revs]

00:21:16.314 --> 00:21:19.150
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:20.193 --> 00:21:21.569
[breathes deeply]

00:21:22.820 --> 00:21:24.906
Okay. Let's see what you got.

00:21:32.205 --> 00:21:37.377
If he raced with Ruben,
he raced with Schumacher. With Senna.

00:21:39.754 --> 00:21:43.132
♪ I tried changing my reality ♪

00:21:43.758 --> 00:21:46.761
♪ But I don't think
It's gonna set me free ♪

00:21:47.762 --> 00:21:50.557
♪ There's only one thing I can guarantee ♪

00:21:50.640 --> 00:21:55.019
♪ And that's
I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:55.812 --> 00:21:58.523
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:21:59.232 --> 00:22:02.694
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:22:03.194 --> 00:22:07.365
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:22:07.448 --> 00:22:09.242
All right, pull up Joshua's sector times.

00:22:19.043 --> 00:22:20.753
Twenty quid says he stacks it.

00:22:20.837 --> 00:22:22.463
Make it a hundred, you're on.

00:22:23.381 --> 00:22:24.632
Oh, shit.

00:22:24.716 --> 00:22:26.843
-[laughs]
-[laughs]

00:22:26.926 --> 00:22:30.096
Sorry, uh, this is Hugh Nickleby,
your race engineer.

00:22:30.180 --> 00:22:32.182
Good morning, Hugh.
How are my tire temps looking?

00:22:32.265 --> 00:22:35.101
Yep, almost warm. End of the lap,
you should be good to push.

00:22:35.185 --> 00:22:36.644
[exhales deeply]

00:22:38.104 --> 00:22:39.105
[grunts]

00:22:40.190 --> 00:22:41.274
[exhales deeply]

00:22:44.569 --> 00:22:46.863
[tires squeal]

00:22:50.658 --> 00:22:52.660
[sighs]

00:22:52.744 --> 00:22:54.495
Right. Man.

00:22:55.538 --> 00:22:57.248
-[Sonny] Hugh?
-Yes, sir?

00:22:57.332 --> 00:22:59.292
-You should've taken that bet.
-[chuckles]

00:22:59.375 --> 00:23:00.710
-[sighs]
-[Hugh] Copy that.

00:23:01.336 --> 00:23:05.006
♪ No one's accusing me of sanity ♪

00:23:05.798 --> 00:23:09.385
♪ I ain't everybody's cup of tea ♪

00:23:10.053 --> 00:23:11.847
♪ But that's the facts
I'm talkin' factually ♪

00:23:11.930 --> 00:23:13.097
Going for a lap.

00:23:14.057 --> 00:23:16.476
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:16.559 --> 00:23:20.939
♪ Yes, I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:21.022 --> 00:23:24.859
♪ Whoa, I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:25.443 --> 00:23:29.614
♪ I'm just as bad as I used to be ♪

00:23:31.074 --> 00:23:33.159
Nope. Shit.

00:23:33.243 --> 00:23:34.244
He's dead.

00:23:34.327 --> 00:23:37.038
Come on. Don't do that.

00:23:37.121 --> 00:23:38.748
[all groan]

00:23:38.831 --> 00:23:39.832
And buried.

00:24:16.953 --> 00:24:18.329
[grunts]

00:24:19.497 --> 00:24:20.582
Wait.

00:24:22.584 --> 00:24:23.960
Wait.

00:24:24.878 --> 00:24:26.171
[inhales sharply]

00:24:26.963 --> 00:24:28.381
Now.

00:24:28.464 --> 00:24:29.465
[grunts]

00:24:31.885 --> 00:24:33.178
The car is there, come on.

00:24:37.432 --> 00:24:39.100
He's gaining.

00:24:39.184 --> 00:24:40.393
Ah, shit.

00:24:41.269 --> 00:24:43.897
-[tires squealing]
-[grunts]

00:24:49.194 --> 00:24:51.821
[grunts, groans]

00:24:51.905 --> 00:24:52.906
[song ends]

00:24:52.989 --> 00:24:54.741
-[grunts]
-You okay?

00:24:54.824 --> 00:24:57.368
[groans] Yep. All good.

00:24:57.452 --> 00:25:00.997
-[laughs]
-[sirens wailing]

00:25:01.080 --> 00:25:03.708
[grunting]

00:25:09.881 --> 00:25:12.258
-[groans, sighs]
-[Kaspar] Oh!

00:25:13.009 --> 00:25:15.970
-[Kate] Come on.
-[Sonny pants]

00:25:16.054 --> 00:25:17.430
Yeah, she's got something.

00:25:17.514 --> 00:25:18.973
Yeah, you mean had something.

00:25:20.308 --> 00:25:22.602
But definitely snappy
in the high-speed corners.

00:25:22.685 --> 00:25:23.937
Unpredictable in the lows.

00:25:24.896 --> 00:25:26.981
Had trouble with the
rears, turns 14, 16...

00:25:27.065 --> 00:25:28.566
And the final turn, maybe?

00:25:28.650 --> 00:25:30.860
-No, that's on me.
-What was his lap time?

00:25:31.528 --> 00:25:36.282
He passed his entirely self-imposed test
by five hundredths of a second.

00:25:38.785 --> 00:25:40.245
[sighs] Huh.

00:25:40.828 --> 00:25:41.955
[chuckles]

00:25:43.414 --> 00:25:44.457
Well… [sighs]

00:25:46.334 --> 00:25:47.544
…it's a start.

00:25:47.627 --> 00:25:49.170
[scoffs]

00:25:50.505 --> 00:25:52.507
[laid-back music playing]

00:25:56.469 --> 00:26:00.181
Bro, we got nine races to catch
the eye of another team, you know.

00:26:00.849 --> 00:26:02.684
And as your manager, I have to advise you

00:26:02.767 --> 00:26:05.228
that we need to start hitting
these social and sponsor events.

00:26:05.311 --> 00:26:06.938
You need more engagement, Josh,
more followers.

00:26:07.021 --> 00:26:09.421
-All right, deal.
-All right, cool. I'm just saying, innit?

00:26:10.275 --> 00:26:11.401
You eaten? I'm starving.

00:26:11.943 --> 00:26:12.944
Nah.

00:26:13.444 --> 00:26:14.696
Gotta see someone though.

00:26:14.779 --> 00:26:17.490
Yeah? Hey, take a picture, post that shit.

00:26:17.574 --> 00:26:19.117
Send it to me, I'll post that shit.

00:26:19.200 --> 00:26:20.618
It's my mum.

00:26:20.702 --> 00:26:22.287
Don't you dare post that shit.

00:26:22.370 --> 00:26:23.454
[laughs]

00:26:23.538 --> 00:26:25.498
I knew you was gonna say that.

00:26:28.918 --> 00:26:30.378
[music ends]

00:26:30.461 --> 00:26:31.713
[music plays softly on radio]

00:26:31.796 --> 00:26:33.047
[phone chimes]

00:26:36.551 --> 00:26:38.511
-[clicks tongue, sighs]
-Okay, baby?

00:26:39.012 --> 00:26:40.680
Yeah. Just tired.

00:26:41.514 --> 00:26:43.057
Bad tires or the engine?

00:26:43.975 --> 00:26:45.519
Come on, Mum.
You don't know about the cars.

00:26:45.602 --> 00:26:47.812
[chuckles] Facety.

00:26:47.896 --> 00:26:51.274
All right, I may not know much about cars,
but I know a lot about you.

00:26:51.941 --> 00:26:52.942
Go.

00:26:54.235 --> 00:26:55.403
[sighs]

00:26:55.486 --> 00:26:57.947
I might lose my seat
if the team don't win a race.

00:26:58.948 --> 00:26:59.949
Any race.

00:27:00.783 --> 00:27:01.868
There are other teams?

00:27:01.951 --> 00:27:03.791
Yeah, there's 20 seats,
but they're all filled.

00:27:04.662 --> 00:27:06.831
Plus, there's this new guy, and… [sighs]

00:27:06.915 --> 00:27:07.916
…he's old.

00:27:07.999 --> 00:27:09.167
How old?

00:27:09.250 --> 00:27:11.753
Like, really old. Like… 80.

00:27:11.836 --> 00:27:13.588
[laughs]

00:27:15.256 --> 00:27:17.008
He's such an arsehole, Mum.

00:27:17.717 --> 00:27:18.968
He's quick, though.

00:27:19.552 --> 00:27:20.929
Don't mind that.

00:27:21.012 --> 00:27:22.555
Focus on you.

00:27:22.639 --> 00:27:24.850
You can spend your whole life
worrying about other people,

00:27:24.933 --> 00:27:27.310
but your time is right now.

00:27:29.270 --> 00:27:30.396
You still love it?

00:27:31.940 --> 00:27:33.274
Course I still love it.

00:27:33.358 --> 00:27:35.568
Then remember what
your father used to say.

00:27:36.444 --> 00:27:38.905
"Put your head down and drive."

00:27:40.073 --> 00:27:41.074
Yes, ma'am.

00:27:41.157 --> 00:27:42.909
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

00:27:42.992 --> 00:27:44.285
[jaunty music playing]

00:27:58.049 --> 00:28:00.260
-[bells ring]
-[cows moo]

00:28:03.596 --> 00:28:05.265
[bicycle bell rings]

00:28:05.348 --> 00:28:07.934
[herder 1] Come on, then. It's all good.
Come on. Come on, then.

00:28:08.017 --> 00:28:09.811
Come on. Come on.

00:28:10.436 --> 00:28:12.480
-Come here. Come on, then.
-You're kiddin' me.

00:28:12.564 --> 00:28:14.649
[herders clamoring]

00:28:14.732 --> 00:28:17.402
[herder 2] Don't park there.
It's just a car. Quieten down.

00:28:17.485 --> 00:28:18.736
Come on, eh? Come on.

00:28:25.034 --> 00:28:26.369
[music ends]

00:28:28.162 --> 00:28:30.540
Thought your job was to build
the fastest car on the planet.

00:28:31.165 --> 00:28:33.585
[chuckles] My job is wind.

00:28:34.460 --> 00:28:36.462
So, helps to feel it.

00:28:37.797 --> 00:28:38.798
Mmm. [sighs]

00:28:38.882 --> 00:28:40.300
["Bright Lights" playing]

00:28:40.383 --> 00:28:42.760
Mysterious moves at Apex GP,

00:28:42.844 --> 00:28:46.514
who have finally announced the driver
who will take their second seat.

00:28:46.598 --> 00:28:49.726
And in a bizarre twist,
it's American Sonny Hayes,

00:28:49.809 --> 00:28:53.062
who hasn't raced in Formula 1
for over three decades.

00:28:53.146 --> 00:28:54.856
Son of an IndyCar mechanic,

00:28:54.939 --> 00:28:58.401
Hayes was considered something
of a reckless young phenomenon,

00:28:58.484 --> 00:29:00.737
the greatest who never was.

00:29:00.820 --> 00:29:03.615
His former career
being brought to an abrupt halt

00:29:03.698 --> 00:29:06.492
by a horrific accident
at the Spanish Grand Prix.

00:29:07.035 --> 00:29:10.246
He reappeared a decade later
in racing championships

00:29:10.330 --> 00:29:13.666
as diverse as Le Mans,
NASCAR, the Dakar Rally,

00:29:13.750 --> 00:29:16.628
and even a stint as
a New York taxi driver.

00:29:16.711 --> 00:29:18.630
-Oh, no.
-[crowd applauding]

00:29:18.713 --> 00:29:20.715
[Will Buxton] But now he's back
racing for a team which has,

00:29:20.798 --> 00:29:25.303
in its entire F1 history,
never even finished in the top ten.

00:29:25.386 --> 00:29:27.305
None of this will dampen speculation

00:29:27.388 --> 00:29:31.726
that majority shareholder Cervantes
Capital are looking to sell the team.

00:29:31.809 --> 00:29:34.479
And if they do,
that will likely also bring an end

00:29:34.562 --> 00:29:37.273
to the career of F1 rookie Joshua Pearce.

00:29:37.357 --> 00:29:39.109
-Can we go now?
-"Desperate times," they say,

00:29:39.192 --> 00:29:40.568
"call for desperate measures,"

00:29:40.652 --> 00:29:43.404
but I honestly cannot recall
a driver signing

00:29:43.488 --> 00:29:45.448
-quite as desperate as this.
-Let's go.

00:29:46.699 --> 00:29:49.327
Boy, look at my son.

00:29:49.410 --> 00:29:51.371
-[Joshua] Huh? [chuckles]
-Hey. [laughs]

00:29:51.454 --> 00:29:53.165
-[manager] That's the one.
-[Joshua's mom] Huh.

00:29:53.248 --> 00:29:55.458
-[music ends]
-That's the other driver?

00:29:55.542 --> 00:29:58.294
Yep. That's him and his stupid face.

00:29:58.378 --> 00:30:00.880
But, wait, you said he was old.
He not that old.

00:30:00.964 --> 00:30:02.382
[manager] Hey, Josh.

00:30:02.465 --> 00:30:03.967
You want a next shot anywhere?

00:30:04.050 --> 00:30:06.970
Nine races means nine times
you have to beat Chuck Norris.

00:30:09.013 --> 00:30:11.266
For now, start by winning over the press.

00:30:11.349 --> 00:30:13.434
-Yeah? You ready?
-Mm-hmm.

00:30:13.518 --> 00:30:14.644
Cool. Let's go.

00:30:15.186 --> 00:30:16.187
-[sighs]
-Mmm.

00:30:16.271 --> 00:30:19.315
That's a handsome man right there.
[chuckles]

00:30:21.067 --> 00:30:26.447
[Will Buxton] Joshua. Hey. Um, it's been
an undeniably messy start to your season.

00:30:26.531 --> 00:30:32.370
No wins, car problems throughout,
and now you have another new teammate.

00:30:32.453 --> 00:30:34.163
How exactly are you finding it?

00:30:34.956 --> 00:30:37.917
Messy start doesn't mean
you can't finish neat. All right?

00:30:38.001 --> 00:30:41.754
Apex have a fire crew of engineers,
so I'm confident we'll come back fightin'.

00:30:41.838 --> 00:30:43.715
In terms of new teammates,

00:30:44.507 --> 00:30:47.927
I think it's really wonderful that Apex
are giving second chances to the elderly.

00:30:48.011 --> 00:30:50.013
[all laugh]

00:30:50.096 --> 00:30:52.807
Ah, yes. Next question.
Thank you. Yes, Don. Yeah.

00:30:53.558 --> 00:30:56.477
Mr. Hayes. Hi. Don Cavendish.
Um, welcome back to the UK.

00:30:56.561 --> 00:30:57.896
It's been a while, mmm?

00:30:57.979 --> 00:30:59.606
I mean, last time
you raced at Silverstone,

00:30:59.689 --> 00:31:03.193
Bill Clinton was your president,
and we were all dancing the Macarena.

00:31:03.276 --> 00:31:05.904
-So, uh, it must be surreal to be back.
-[reporters laugh]

00:31:08.198 --> 00:31:09.240
Yeah.

00:31:11.367 --> 00:31:13.995
And, uh, during that decade,
you gave up racing,

00:31:14.078 --> 00:31:16.080
and, uh, gambled professionally?

00:31:16.164 --> 00:31:17.165
Uh-huh.

00:31:17.790 --> 00:31:20.543
Before declaring yourself
personally bankrupt?

00:31:20.627 --> 00:31:21.920
Yep.

00:31:22.003 --> 00:31:24.923
[Don] You had a marriage annulled
and two more ended in divorce?

00:31:25.006 --> 00:31:26.341
Yep.

00:31:28.134 --> 00:31:29.844
Anything you wish you'd done differently?

00:31:31.638 --> 00:31:32.639
Yeah.

00:31:32.722 --> 00:31:34.891
[reporters murmuring]

00:31:35.975 --> 00:31:38.478
[chuckles] No more questions.
Thank you. Yes. Thank you.

00:31:38.561 --> 00:31:42.982
[reporters clamoring]

00:31:43.066 --> 00:31:45.610
[somber orchestral music playing]

00:31:51.658 --> 00:31:54.327
[grunts]

00:32:01.793 --> 00:32:03.003
[music becomes electronic, dramatic]

00:32:03.086 --> 00:32:04.295
[panting]

00:32:04.379 --> 00:32:07.632
[breathing heavily]

00:32:07.715 --> 00:32:10.009
[grunts]

00:32:10.093 --> 00:32:12.178
[grunting]

00:32:13.972 --> 00:32:16.140
[sighs]

00:32:38.204 --> 00:32:41.332
[people chattering]

00:32:57.098 --> 00:32:58.099
[Joshua] Yes, Dodge.

00:33:01.978 --> 00:33:03.229
What time was he here?

00:33:03.313 --> 00:33:04.355
Before me.

00:33:11.154 --> 00:33:13.323
-And before you.
-[Joshua sighs]

00:33:13.406 --> 00:33:14.490
[music fades]

00:33:14.574 --> 00:33:17.243
[people cheering]

00:33:17.327 --> 00:33:19.329
[ball bouncing in distance]

00:33:20.538 --> 00:33:21.873
[sighs]

00:33:25.084 --> 00:33:27.337
Okay, here he comes. Apologize.

00:33:27.420 --> 00:33:29.047
[scoffs] Apologize? I can't do that.

00:33:29.547 --> 00:33:32.342
-How you mean? Why not?
-Because it's a sign of weakness.

00:33:32.425 --> 00:33:33.468
It's a sign of strength.

00:33:33.551 --> 00:33:34.761
Sign of weakness.

00:33:35.303 --> 00:33:36.888
You hard ears, just do it.

00:33:36.971 --> 00:33:38.223
Mum, I can't.

00:33:38.306 --> 00:33:39.891
You can. You will.

00:33:40.558 --> 00:33:41.559
[sighs]

00:33:44.604 --> 00:33:45.813
[sucks teeth]

00:33:48.107 --> 00:33:49.317
[sighs]

00:33:52.195 --> 00:33:53.196
Hey, man.

00:33:54.697 --> 00:33:57.325
Other day at the press conference,
stuff I said wasn't cool.

00:33:58.743 --> 00:34:00.870
[muttering] You say sorry.

00:34:00.954 --> 00:34:06.042
So, basically what I'm trying to say is…
I'm sorry.

00:34:06.125 --> 00:34:09.087
It's all right. You're just worried I'm
quicker than you. Hi, I'm Sonny.

00:34:09.796 --> 00:34:11.798
Oh, Bernadette Pearce. Nice to meet you.

00:34:12.382 --> 00:34:14.759
Pleasure.
It's all good. I'll see you out there.

00:34:14.842 --> 00:34:16.219
[scoffs]

00:34:16.302 --> 00:34:18.221
[ball bouncing]

00:34:21.766 --> 00:34:23.768
[pop song playing, muffled]

00:34:23.851 --> 00:34:24.853
[sighs]

00:34:26.062 --> 00:34:27.355
[sighs] How are you feeling?

00:34:27.438 --> 00:34:28.940
-So good.
-Good.

00:34:32.193 --> 00:34:33.277
-You good?
-Good.

00:34:33.777 --> 00:34:34.779
Good.

00:34:35.864 --> 00:34:36.864
No pressure.

00:34:36.947 --> 00:34:37.949
None.

00:34:39.117 --> 00:34:40.118
[sighs]

00:34:43.371 --> 00:34:45.248
-Great.
-Great. [clears throat]

00:34:45.331 --> 00:34:46.498
Great.

00:34:47.208 --> 00:34:48.918
[Croft] Welcome along to Silverstone,

00:34:49.002 --> 00:34:54.591
the circuit where on the 13th of May 1950
the Formula 1 World Championship began.

00:34:54.674 --> 00:34:59.304
Today, we kick off the final nine races
of this thrilling championship season

00:34:59.387 --> 00:35:02.557
here at the 77th British Grand Prix.

00:35:02.640 --> 00:35:05.101
[Brundle] As always,
11 teams will take the grid,

00:35:05.185 --> 00:35:07.103
fielding two drivers each.

00:35:07.187 --> 00:35:10.982
With race order determined
by the qualifying times set yesterday.

00:35:11.065 --> 00:35:13.067
Red Bull will start on pole

00:35:13.151 --> 00:35:16.654
followed by the two McLarens
and two Ferraris.

00:35:17.864 --> 00:35:20.283
[Croft] Drivers,
two minutes to national anthem.

00:35:20.366 --> 00:35:22.952
["God Save the King" playing]

00:35:36.925 --> 00:35:38.927
[marching band playing]

00:35:45.475 --> 00:35:47.727
["We Will Rock You" playing]

00:35:49.187 --> 00:35:50.271
Sonny!

00:35:51.189 --> 00:35:53.024
Ah, Ruben.
Don't make me talk to the money.

00:35:53.107 --> 00:35:55.360
Come on, give me a moment.
Just smile and shake hands.

00:35:55.443 --> 00:35:57.111
He's an important member of the board.

00:35:57.195 --> 00:35:58.655
Sonny, this is Peter Banning,

00:35:58.738 --> 00:35:59.948
-one of my investors.
-Hi.

00:36:00.031 --> 00:36:01.032
Hi.

00:36:01.115 --> 00:36:03.076
He knows absolutely nothing about racing…

00:36:03.159 --> 00:36:05.703
-Yeah.
-…but he's my eyes and ears on the board.

00:36:05.787 --> 00:36:08.164
And, uh, you're Ruben's Hail Mary.

00:36:08.248 --> 00:36:09.916
Now, that is
an American football term, right?

00:36:09.999 --> 00:36:11.543
The Hail Mary, the long shot. The...

00:36:11.626 --> 00:36:13.044
I believe it's a religious term,
originally.

00:36:13.127 --> 00:36:14.129
That is true. That is true.

00:36:14.212 --> 00:36:15.922
I'm praying to them all.

00:36:16.005 --> 00:36:18.258
I'm the one guy on the board
who actually wants to keep the team.

00:36:18.341 --> 00:36:20.177
The rest are calling it, you know,
Ruben's Inferno.

00:36:20.260 --> 00:36:21.970
But, seriously, man, I'm hooked.

00:36:22.053 --> 00:36:24.514
I've binged all of Drive to Survive.

00:36:24.597 --> 00:36:27.684
I honestly don't think I've ever known
so much about car tires. It's incredible.

00:36:27.767 --> 00:36:28.935
I'm gonna get back to my day job.

00:36:29.018 --> 00:36:30.770
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:36:30.854 --> 00:36:32.188
["We Will Rock You" continues]

00:36:32.272 --> 00:36:34.440
Hey, man.
We're counting on you. Good luck.

00:37:33.041 --> 00:37:34.834
What are you doing here, Sonny?

00:37:50.808 --> 00:37:53.436
[Croft] And as the clock ticks then
to the top of the hour,

00:37:53.520 --> 00:37:56.272
it's time to get things going here
at Silverstone.

00:37:56.356 --> 00:37:57.982
It's formation lap first.

00:37:58.066 --> 00:38:03.071
One tour of the track and a chance for the
drivers to warm up their tires and brakes.

00:38:05.907 --> 00:38:08.493
[Brundle] Oh, no.
There's a problem for Apex.

00:38:08.576 --> 00:38:11.829
That's Hayes in P22. His car hasn't moved.

00:38:11.913 --> 00:38:13.998
Hang on. I got power trouble.

00:38:14.082 --> 00:38:16.501
It's start mode, Sonny.

00:38:16.584 --> 00:38:17.919
Start mode on.

00:38:18.002 --> 00:38:20.004
[Brundle] Yes,
a lesson for everyone at home.

00:38:20.088 --> 00:38:22.131
New car? Do read the manual.

00:38:22.215 --> 00:38:24.593
[Croft] It's been a while since he was
out on the track. At this rate…

00:38:24.676 --> 00:38:26.761
-Dios mío.
-…he's not even gonna get into the race.

00:38:26.845 --> 00:38:27.846
Ay.

00:38:29.389 --> 00:38:30.473
-I got it.
-[engine revs]

00:38:30.557 --> 00:38:31.558
All good.

00:38:33.560 --> 00:38:36.229
[Croft] And he's away at last.
Thank goodness for that.

00:38:36.312 --> 00:38:38.690
[Brundle] If he falls too far behind
on the formation lap…

00:38:38.773 --> 00:38:39.775
-Drink?
-…he'll be at risk…

00:38:39.858 --> 00:38:42.277
-Eh? No.
-…of having to start in the pit lane.

00:38:43.444 --> 00:38:45.989
Where's Sonny? He's holding us up.

00:38:46.072 --> 00:38:48.408
Yeah. Just checking, Joshua.
Just checking.

00:38:49.576 --> 00:38:51.536
-What's wrong with his car?
-What? Nothing.

00:38:51.619 --> 00:38:53.037
[Brundle] With a clear track ahead,

00:38:53.121 --> 00:38:56.332
Hayes has been able
to push much harder on this formation lap.

00:38:56.416 --> 00:38:59.836
He'll turn up at the back of the grid
with warm tires, ready to go.

00:39:01.004 --> 00:39:03.548
Cheeky shit. It's on purpose.

00:39:08.428 --> 00:39:09.762
What is this guy doing?

00:39:09.846 --> 00:39:13.725
[Croft] This is actually now
turning into an advantage for Sonny Hayes.

00:39:13.808 --> 00:39:17.937
[Brundle] And he's just made it in time.
Watch out for his start.

00:39:26.905 --> 00:39:31.075
[Croft] Five lights ahead of the drivers.
It's lights out and away we go!

00:39:31.159 --> 00:39:32.285
[crowd cheering]

00:39:44.130 --> 00:39:46.341
Here comes Sonny Hayes,
ladies and gentlemen.

00:39:46.424 --> 00:39:50.220
Using those warm tires to carve his way
through the back of the field.

00:39:50.303 --> 00:39:53.181
[Brundle] And if you ever need
confidence in your car,

00:39:53.264 --> 00:39:54.724
it's here at Silverstone.

00:40:11.533 --> 00:40:13.451
Hayes is just sailing past people.

00:40:13.535 --> 00:40:16.454
He's moved up seven places
since the start.

00:40:16.538 --> 00:40:19.374
-Apex GP has struggled with this car…
-Yes!

00:40:19.457 --> 00:40:21.751
…but they've brought an upgrade package
this weekend.

00:40:21.835 --> 00:40:25.755
Let's see if it makes a difference
as Hayes attacks Perez in the Red Bull.

00:40:29.676 --> 00:40:32.554
Car's bouncing around this dirty air.
I can't position to attack.

00:40:33.346 --> 00:40:35.723
[Brundle] Hayes complaining
about his car over the radio.

00:40:35.807 --> 00:40:38.560
That's not what the team wants to hear.

00:40:38.643 --> 00:40:41.813
Copy. Gap is 0.9 to Perez.
You're within DRS range.

00:40:41.896 --> 00:40:44.065
Should be able to take him
on the next straight.

00:40:46.734 --> 00:40:50.280
[Croft] Hayes now using
the drag reduction system to get past.

00:40:50.363 --> 00:40:51.781
-[cheering]
-Yeah!

00:40:51.865 --> 00:40:54.033
Won't be able to hold him off, guys.
I got no grip.

00:40:54.117 --> 00:40:56.119
-This is trouble now for Apex GP.
-Oh, come on.

00:40:56.202 --> 00:40:57.954
The Red Bull's tires are now warm

00:40:58.037 --> 00:41:01.583
and Hayes hasn't got his tire advantage
from the start anymore.

00:41:01.666 --> 00:41:05.044
We've seen the attack.
Now it's all about defense.

00:41:05.128 --> 00:41:07.839
And Perez on the attack into Vale.

00:41:07.922 --> 00:41:11.217
Hayes is in trouble.
This could be the places reversed.

00:41:11.301 --> 00:41:13.261
-[crowd cheering]
-And it is.

00:41:13.344 --> 00:41:14.345
Damn.

00:41:14.429 --> 00:41:16.472
Rear end is loose.
Tell me if you see a fix.

00:41:16.556 --> 00:41:19.350
Tell him to pull back the entry
to get a better exit.

00:41:19.434 --> 00:41:21.644
He-He thinks it's the setup. It's not.

00:41:24.022 --> 00:41:25.148
[Croft] Twenty laps down.

00:41:25.231 --> 00:41:29.152
Verstappen leads but Joshua Pearce
is struggling out there at the moment.

00:41:29.235 --> 00:41:32.113
Guys, get me off these softs.
I'm going backwards.

00:41:32.197 --> 00:41:34.949
Copy that. Lap 20. Box, box.

00:41:35.033 --> 00:41:37.452
[Brundle] Stakes couldn't be higher
for rookie Joshua Pearce.

00:41:37.535 --> 00:41:41.164
This is not where you want to be,
in last place.

00:41:43.583 --> 00:41:45.168
[groans] I'm jammed. Back up!

00:41:52.258 --> 00:41:53.635
Hit something. What was that?

00:41:53.718 --> 00:41:54.719
[crowd shrieks]

00:41:54.802 --> 00:41:57.263
[Croft] Ooh, a seven-second pit stop.

00:41:57.347 --> 00:41:59.390
Apex GP won't be happy with that.

00:41:59.474 --> 00:42:02.393
That's double the time it should've taken.

00:42:02.477 --> 00:42:04.020
Lost the rears. Box, box.

00:42:04.103 --> 00:42:06.022
Copy. Go to plan B. Box, box.

00:42:06.731 --> 00:42:09.442
[Croft] And here comes Sonny Hayes
for a fresh set of tires.

00:42:09.526 --> 00:42:14.280
He'll be hoping these will help him
hold on to his current position of P15.

00:42:14.364 --> 00:42:15.281
Front jacks! Front jacks!

00:42:15.365 --> 00:42:16.992
[Brundle] The front jack has
not worked properly.

00:42:17.075 --> 00:42:20.328
-You're kidding me.
-This is causing absolute pandemonium

00:42:20.411 --> 00:42:22.705
in the Apex GP pit lane.

00:42:24.541 --> 00:42:27.919
Whatever could go wrong
is going wrong for this team.

00:42:31.089 --> 00:42:34.676
[Croft] And coming out of the pit,
Hayes just ahead of his teammate.

00:42:34.759 --> 00:42:39.222
As Pearce and Hayes go battling it out
here at Silverstone.

00:42:39.305 --> 00:42:40.557
Coming for you, old man.

00:42:47.939 --> 00:42:49.732
Got the pace, man.
Tell him to let me pass.

00:42:49.816 --> 00:42:51.485
Yeah. Copy. Hold position. Stand by. Kate.

00:42:51.568 --> 00:42:54.320
Josh is faster. Sonny is on cold tires.

00:42:59.826 --> 00:43:01.706
Yeah, okay, Sonny, no fighting.
Let him through.

00:43:07.000 --> 00:43:09.127
Sonny, no fighting.

00:43:09.210 --> 00:43:10.670
Who's fighting? I'm racing.

00:43:10.753 --> 00:43:13.131
[Croft] Pearce on the inside,
Hayes on the outside.

00:43:13.214 --> 00:43:15.550
[Brundle] Hayes trying
to make him eat concrete

00:43:15.633 --> 00:43:17.302
up against the old pit wall there.

00:43:17.385 --> 00:43:19.554
Joshua, you're gonna
have to fight for position.

00:43:19.637 --> 00:43:20.638
You are racing Sonny.

00:43:20.722 --> 00:43:21.806
A-ffirm.

00:43:21.890 --> 00:43:24.392
[Brundle] They're giving
absolutely no quarter.

00:43:24.475 --> 00:43:26.394
No benefit to their teammate at all.

00:43:26.477 --> 00:43:29.147
They're pushing as if
they're trying to win a Grand Prix.

00:43:29.230 --> 00:43:32.442
[Croft] But this is the battle
for last place, remember?

00:43:32.525 --> 00:43:33.693
And what a brawl it is.

00:43:33.776 --> 00:43:35.195
Let's go, kid. Bring it.

00:43:38.740 --> 00:43:40.491
What is this guy doing? Let me through.

00:43:40.575 --> 00:43:42.785
[crowd cheering]

00:43:50.710 --> 00:43:51.753
[spectators gasp]

00:43:56.925 --> 00:43:58.760
[Croft] Round the final corner.

00:43:58.843 --> 00:43:59.969
It's close!

00:44:00.053 --> 00:44:01.596
They make contact.

00:44:01.679 --> 00:44:05.141
- Both Apex GP cars into the gravel,
- [Sonny grunts]

00:44:05.225 --> 00:44:07.227
and Pearce hits the barrier.

00:44:07.310 --> 00:44:09.270
[crowd clamoring]

00:44:09.354 --> 00:44:10.605
-Ah, no!
-No!

00:44:11.314 --> 00:44:12.482
[Brundle] This is mad.

00:44:12.565 --> 00:44:14.776
The cardinal sin of motor racing.

00:44:14.859 --> 00:44:16.486
-A double DNF.
-[Ruben groans]

00:44:16.569 --> 00:44:20.448
Just when it couldn't get any worse
for the black and gold.

00:44:20.532 --> 00:44:22.692
-[Peter] That's a tough one, man.
-[mutters, sighing]

00:44:27.789 --> 00:44:30.166
[crowd shrieking, booing]

00:44:38.550 --> 00:44:39.843
We can't corner.

00:44:39.926 --> 00:44:42.512
We're bouncing around the place
like we're on the bloody Tube

00:44:42.595 --> 00:44:45.035
and now we think it's cool
to leave wheel guns in the pit box.

00:44:45.431 --> 00:44:46.432
Who even was that?

00:44:46.516 --> 00:44:48.685
-That was me.
-Of course.

00:44:51.312 --> 00:44:52.313
Old man.

00:44:55.275 --> 00:44:57.944
You losing your hearing? What was that?

00:44:58.945 --> 00:44:59.946
You wanna do this here?

00:45:00.029 --> 00:45:02.324
Yeah, I'd love to do this here
in front of the team, right.

00:45:02.407 --> 00:45:03.742
The one that you're apparently a part of.

00:45:03.825 --> 00:45:06.578
-Okay. You made a mistake. It happens.
-[laughs]

00:45:06.661 --> 00:45:08.329
I made a mistake. I love this guy, man.

00:45:08.413 --> 00:45:10.791
-Don't worry about it, Jodie.
-Are you even listening to me?

00:45:10.874 --> 00:45:12.750
-Not really.
-[Kaspar] No!

00:45:12.834 --> 00:45:14.169
Stop.

00:45:14.252 --> 00:45:15.670
Joshua is right.

00:45:15.753 --> 00:45:17.338
An order is an order.

00:45:17.422 --> 00:45:20.258
May I remind you that you report to me?

00:45:23.928 --> 00:45:24.929
Cool.

00:45:25.722 --> 00:45:27.640
Just don't ask me to give up position.

00:45:30.685 --> 00:45:32.604
Sorry. Sorry, guys.

00:45:34.731 --> 00:45:36.357
Hold up.

00:45:36.441 --> 00:45:38.026
You swan into our garage
like some entitled prick.

00:45:38.109 --> 00:45:39.903
-"Swan"?
-Calling us piss poor…

00:45:39.986 --> 00:45:41.613
-What's "swan"?
-…and then you drive like that. Huh?

00:45:41.696 --> 00:45:43.573
You said I "swan." What's that mean?

00:45:43.656 --> 00:45:46.367
You. You're an arsehole.
You come in like an arsehole. You swan.

00:45:46.451 --> 00:45:48.119
So swans are assholes?

00:45:50.163 --> 00:45:52.916
You're making the mistake of thinking
that I'm just gonna be some grateful kid

00:45:52.999 --> 00:45:54.751
who'll bend a knee to an old-timer.

00:45:55.418 --> 00:45:57.629
I climbed a mountain to get here, bro.

00:45:58.421 --> 00:45:59.506
Formula 1.

00:45:59.589 --> 00:46:02.342
Back home we call that
a participation trophy.

00:46:02.425 --> 00:46:04.344
[reporters] Joshua, Joshua! Josh!

00:46:04.427 --> 00:46:05.470
[clamoring]

00:46:05.553 --> 00:46:07.472
[chuckles] Yeah.

00:46:08.806 --> 00:46:11.142
What the hell are you smiling about, man?

00:46:11.226 --> 00:46:12.393
Did you win something?

00:46:12.936 --> 00:46:15.188
There's 20 other drivers
still out on that track

00:46:15.271 --> 00:46:17.273
and you're in here
posing for that nonsense.

00:46:17.357 --> 00:46:20.276
Do you think any of them respect us?
Do you?

00:46:21.402 --> 00:46:24.739
They need to learn that
no one gets past us without a fight.

00:46:24.822 --> 00:46:25.823
No one.

00:46:28.826 --> 00:46:31.579
You don't like the way I'm driving?
Beat me, swan.

00:46:38.920 --> 00:46:39.921
Hell of a race, huh?

00:46:40.463 --> 00:46:41.589
Whoo!

00:46:52.392 --> 00:46:55.854
[breathes deeply]

00:46:59.983 --> 00:47:03.194
Sorry, I didn't see you. Um… [sighs]

00:47:03.945 --> 00:47:05.947
[sighs] You still beating yourself up?

00:47:06.030 --> 00:47:07.240
Yeah.

00:47:07.323 --> 00:47:09.409
Yeah, I know that one. [chuckles]

00:47:11.744 --> 00:47:14.622
Um, thanks for what you said out there.

00:47:16.124 --> 00:47:18.877
Just don't do it again, okay?

00:47:19.586 --> 00:47:21.171
Makes me look like I need help.

00:47:21.880 --> 00:47:24.716
Oh, man. You're right. [sighs] Got it.

00:47:25.300 --> 00:47:28.386
Hey, for what it's worth,
don't be shitty to yourself.

00:47:28.469 --> 00:47:30.472
There's plenty of people out there
that'll do that for you.

00:47:30.555 --> 00:47:31.806
Yeah.

00:47:36.686 --> 00:47:37.854
[sighs]

00:47:40.273 --> 00:47:44.903
"I'm sorry, Ruben, for demolishing not one
but both of your lovely cars.

00:47:44.986 --> 00:47:47.447
For coming back into your life
only to destroy it."

00:47:47.530 --> 00:47:48.865
Is this your revenge for Monaco?

00:47:48.948 --> 00:47:50.366
Yeah, I waited 30 years

00:47:50.450 --> 00:47:53.786
and came all this way
to humiliate myself on global television.

00:47:53.870 --> 00:47:57.207
Funny. You think I brought you in
to make my other driver quit?

00:47:57.916 --> 00:48:01.377
Listen, he's cocky.
He's arrogant. He's got a lot to learn.

00:48:01.461 --> 00:48:03.463
[laughs]

00:48:05.006 --> 00:48:07.842
You were cocky, you were arrogant
and you had a lot to learn.

00:48:07.926 --> 00:48:10.678
I'm not here to hold anyone's hand.
I'm here to race.

00:48:10.762 --> 00:48:13.681
No, you're not, Sonny.
You're here to give me a heart attack.

00:48:14.933 --> 00:48:16.559
The board is up my ass

00:48:17.936 --> 00:48:20.355
and I have to decide
whether to continue this fiasco

00:48:20.438 --> 00:48:23.149
-or pull the plug now.
-You have till the end of the season.

00:48:23.233 --> 00:48:25.985
By which time Apex will be worth less
than my shoes!

00:48:26.694 --> 00:48:28.446
Sonny! God…

00:48:31.157 --> 00:48:32.200
Tell me about Kate.

00:48:33.701 --> 00:48:35.370
The car.
I wanna talk to her about the car.

00:48:35.453 --> 00:48:37.956
She's the world's first
female tech director of an F1 team.

00:48:38.039 --> 00:48:39.499
I mean, that takes balls.

00:48:39.582 --> 00:48:41.584
Wow. Is that your line?

00:48:42.168 --> 00:48:43.253
She'll see right through it.

00:48:43.336 --> 00:48:44.462
It's not a line.

00:48:44.546 --> 00:48:46.840
-I'm sorry. Sorry.
-Is she married?

00:48:47.423 --> 00:48:50.635
Okay, stay there in that tub of ice
until Budapest.

00:48:50.718 --> 00:48:52.178
You don't move.

00:48:54.556 --> 00:48:55.723
Hey, Ruben…

00:48:57.809 --> 00:48:59.310
We can't get there with this car.

00:49:08.361 --> 00:49:09.404
[sighs]

00:49:45.732 --> 00:49:47.442
Hey. Hey.

00:49:47.525 --> 00:49:48.943
Yeah, sorry. Hi, hi, hi.

00:49:49.569 --> 00:49:50.570
What you working on?

00:49:51.279 --> 00:49:55.783
I'm working on a new front wing concept.
Trying to pick us up a tenth or so.

00:49:55.867 --> 00:49:59.329
Cool. And you can replicate turns?
Lateral airflow?

00:49:59.412 --> 00:50:01.206
No, just straight line drag.

00:50:01.289 --> 00:50:03.374
But, I mean,
we can calculate it from there.

00:50:04.125 --> 00:50:07.378
Okay, what about turbulent air
from a car we're following?

00:50:07.462 --> 00:50:09.380
No, not exactly, but...

00:50:09.464 --> 00:50:12.258
Track conditions, surface quality,
weather, ambient temps?

00:50:12.342 --> 00:50:16.554
[chuckles] I'm sorry, uh, is there
something that you wanted to discuss?

00:50:16.638 --> 00:50:19.224
Kate, you read my mind.

00:50:23.228 --> 00:50:27.065
So how does one get to be the first female
technical director of an F1 team?

00:50:27.148 --> 00:50:28.316
Must take…

00:50:31.653 --> 00:50:34.656
Dedication and lots of hard work.

00:50:34.739 --> 00:50:38.117
-That's your urgent question?
-Hmm? Mm-mmm.

00:50:38.201 --> 00:50:42.121
Plenty of people think I don't belong here
and I'm happy to add you to the list

00:50:42.205 --> 00:50:43.999
if you're implying
what I… I think you're implying.

00:50:44.082 --> 00:50:45.375
As a rule I don't imply stuff.

00:50:45.458 --> 00:50:46.876
So you like straight talk?

00:50:46.960 --> 00:50:48.711
Straight as an arrow. No sugar.

00:50:49.671 --> 00:50:51.506
Everyone thinks Ruben's lost it.

00:50:51.589 --> 00:50:52.841
That he is clutching at straws.

00:50:52.924 --> 00:50:54.676
They're saying maybe he lost a bet.

00:50:54.759 --> 00:50:57.136
-Ran over your dog.
-[chuckles]

00:50:57.220 --> 00:51:01.808
They're saying Sonny Hayes
isn't a has-been.

00:51:02.308 --> 00:51:03.476
He's a never-was.

00:51:07.063 --> 00:51:09.691
Yeah, when I said I like straight talk
I meant me.

00:51:10.233 --> 00:51:13.528
From others, I mostly prefer praise,
flattery, hero worship,

00:51:13.611 --> 00:51:15.405
at times, straight-up bullshit.

00:51:15.488 --> 00:51:17.866
-Is that what Ruben's for?
-[laughs]

00:51:17.949 --> 00:51:20.326
Ruben. I love the guy.
Most solid, steadfast...

00:51:20.410 --> 00:51:21.786
Said you asked if I was married.

00:51:21.870 --> 00:51:25.248
Disloyal, mean, twisted,
bitter, husk of a man.

00:51:25.331 --> 00:51:31.629
Mmm, yeah. And he also told me about
a big string of ex-wives and girlfriends.

00:51:31.713 --> 00:51:33.298
He said to avoid you like the plague.

00:51:33.381 --> 00:51:36.718
Okay… [chuckles] …let me explain this.

00:51:37.760 --> 00:51:40.096
When you're going 200 miles per hour
into Eau Rouge,

00:51:40.180 --> 00:51:42.348
it's good to know who's got your back.

00:51:43.600 --> 00:51:45.393
And for the record,
in all my years of racing,

00:51:45.476 --> 00:51:49.856
I have never ever hit on
the team technical director.

00:51:49.939 --> 00:51:54.152
[smacks lips] Well, now that's
a huge weight off my mind.

00:51:57.989 --> 00:52:00.241
So what's this urgent question?

00:52:00.325 --> 00:52:01.534
Okay.

00:52:02.410 --> 00:52:05.788
Red Bull, Ferrari,
Mercedes, Aston, now McLaren

00:52:05.872 --> 00:52:07.415
all have us beat on straight line speed.

00:52:07.498 --> 00:52:09.959
Our shot is battling in the turns.

00:52:10.043 --> 00:52:12.754
I need a way
to chase through the dirty air.

00:52:15.215 --> 00:52:19.344
You want me to redesign
so you can follow closer?

00:52:19.427 --> 00:52:20.929
We need to build our car for combat.

00:52:22.013 --> 00:52:24.307
Uh, how am I supposed to make that safe?

00:52:24.390 --> 00:52:25.850
Who said anything about safe?

00:52:28.353 --> 00:52:29.687
That's your question?

00:52:29.771 --> 00:52:30.980
Yeah.

00:52:31.064 --> 00:52:32.273
And here's the straight talk.

00:52:33.441 --> 00:52:34.442
It's urgent.

00:52:36.945 --> 00:52:38.530
[scoffs]

00:52:40.281 --> 00:52:42.867
You know,
I bet when you look in the mirror,

00:52:42.951 --> 00:52:49.415
you see this rough-and-tumble,
old school, no bullshit cowboy.

00:52:49.499 --> 00:52:52.585
Doesn't take orders.
Goes his own way. Huh?

00:52:52.669 --> 00:52:54.087
A lone wolf.

00:52:55.088 --> 00:52:56.589
Well, I have news for you.

00:52:56.673 --> 00:52:59.592
Formula 1 is a team sport. It always was.

00:52:59.676 --> 00:53:02.512
And maybe that's why you failed at it?

00:53:03.638 --> 00:53:07.475
The only question here is,
"Why did Sonny Hayes come back to F1?"

00:53:07.559 --> 00:53:12.146
Now that question
is extremely fucking urgent.

00:53:16.359 --> 00:53:19.779
I'll start listening to you
when you finish a race.

00:53:24.284 --> 00:53:25.285
[grumbles]

00:53:27.287 --> 00:53:28.788
[electronic pop song playing]

00:53:34.544 --> 00:53:36.462
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:42.677 --> 00:53:45.638
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:48.183 --> 00:53:51.019
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:51.102 --> 00:53:52.187
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:53:52.270 --> 00:53:54.772
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:53:54.856 --> 00:53:56.733
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:53:56.816 --> 00:53:59.319
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:53:59.402 --> 00:54:01.029
♪ Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah ♪

00:54:01.112 --> 00:54:05.074
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:54:09.495 --> 00:54:11.789
[song continues]

00:54:12.498 --> 00:54:14.584
♪ Don't let me down ♪

00:54:20.924 --> 00:54:23.718
♪ Don't let me drown ♪

00:54:26.888 --> 00:54:29.265
♪ Nights like these ♪

00:54:29.349 --> 00:54:33.061
♪ There's something mystical
About nights like these ♪

00:54:33.853 --> 00:54:36.356
♪ And the concept of time don't matter ♪

00:54:36.439 --> 00:54:38.066
[song fades]

00:54:38.149 --> 00:54:39.400
[brakes hiss]

00:54:40.652 --> 00:54:44.113
[Buxton] At the Spanish Grand Prix,
the American rookie Sonny Hayes

00:54:44.197 --> 00:54:48.117
had just signed a new contract,
and his future looked very bright.

00:54:48.201 --> 00:54:51.913
He'd earned a reputation
for his aggressive driving style.

00:54:51.996 --> 00:54:55.875
Seen by some as reckless,
it nevertheless served him well

00:54:55.959 --> 00:54:58.711
as he climbed up the order
over the course of the season,

00:54:58.795 --> 00:55:01.798
relentlessly pursuing
his first F1 victory.

00:55:03.508 --> 00:55:06.302
Hayes was running well
in the opening laps,

00:55:06.386 --> 00:55:09.013
chasing down race leader Ayrton Senna.

00:55:09.097 --> 00:55:11.266
However when Hayes made a risky move

00:55:11.349 --> 00:55:15.395
and attacked Senna on the outside of
a high-speed right-hand turn,

00:55:15.979 --> 00:55:19.357
a frightening scene unfolded
as quick as a flash.

00:55:19.440 --> 00:55:21.985
[commentator 1] My goodness!
I just saw him plunge off to the right.

00:55:22.068 --> 00:55:23.612
There you can see the debris on the right.

00:55:23.695 --> 00:55:26.281
What on earth happened there,
I don't know.

00:55:26.364 --> 00:55:27.741
[commentator 2]
Yes, this looks very severe indeed.

00:55:27.824 --> 00:55:31.202
I must say, it looks like, uh, he is…
he really needs help.

00:55:31.286 --> 00:55:33.121
There is nobody coming to him
at the moment.

00:55:33.204 --> 00:55:35.415
The race has been stopped.
The red flag is out.

00:55:35.498 --> 00:55:37.333
This looks a little bit like a...

00:55:54.601 --> 00:55:58.188
[Kate] Our models predict all teams
are gonna be targeting a one-stop race.

00:55:58.271 --> 00:56:02.525
Plan A is to switch from mediums to hards,
between lap 27 and 33.

00:56:02.609 --> 00:56:08.823
Plan B will be medium-hard-medium,
first window 16 to 21, second, 45 to 51.

00:56:08.907 --> 00:56:10.617
Plan C for softs doesn't make sense.

00:56:10.700 --> 00:56:12.911
At this temp,
the tire deg will be too high.

00:56:14.662 --> 00:56:15.663
Nothing else?

00:56:16.247 --> 00:56:18.082
-Yep.
-Yeah, Joshua?

00:56:18.166 --> 00:56:20.293
So, we've just got to
drive our race, all right?

00:56:20.376 --> 00:56:21.378
Let's not try and be heroes.

00:56:21.461 --> 00:56:23.546
Just make it through
those first turns clean.

00:56:23.630 --> 00:56:25.757
Can't win at lap one,
starting at the back,

00:56:25.840 --> 00:56:29.010
so we just gotta hope for some
lucky breaks later on, all right?

00:56:29.093 --> 00:56:30.261
-[crew member] Yeah.
-Yeah.

00:56:30.345 --> 00:56:31.930
Create your own breaks.

00:56:33.264 --> 00:56:35.183
Um, hello, hi? I just said that.

00:56:36.476 --> 00:56:37.769
Hope is not a strategy.

00:56:41.606 --> 00:56:43.024
Anything else, Professor?

00:56:43.942 --> 00:56:45.902
Um… [sighs]

00:56:46.402 --> 00:56:47.487
Drive fast?

00:56:59.791 --> 00:57:03.878
-[crowd cheering]
-[timer beeps]

00:57:03.962 --> 00:57:04.963
[timer stops]

00:57:05.046 --> 00:57:07.298
[Croft] It's lights out, and away we go.

00:57:07.382 --> 00:57:10.051
Great start from Hamilton,
Verstappen battling with him.

00:57:10.134 --> 00:57:13.513
Piastri, Zhou, Leclerc…
and here come the two Apex GPs.

00:57:14.472 --> 00:57:18.893
But Gasly shuts the door,
leaving them with nowhere to go.

00:57:25.275 --> 00:57:28.653
Into turn one,
and there's three cars gone off.

00:57:28.736 --> 00:57:31.865
Gasly, Ocon, and the AlphaTauri, Tsunoda.

00:57:31.948 --> 00:57:33.241
[Sonny] Hit debris. Check my tires.

00:57:33.324 --> 00:57:36.035
Yeah, you've got a puncture. Right rear.
Box. Box this lap.

00:57:36.119 --> 00:57:38.204
First goddamn turn. A ruined race.

00:57:39.163 --> 00:57:41.708
[Sonny] Oh, shit, shit, shit. Ah, shit.

00:57:45.211 --> 00:57:46.713
He's coming in! Let's go.

00:57:47.297 --> 00:57:48.798
[Sonny] Let's go Plan C.

00:57:48.882 --> 00:57:53.261
No, Plan C is for soft tires.
They won't last ten laps in this heat. No.

00:57:53.344 --> 00:57:54.513
That's a negative, Sonny. Plan A.

00:57:54.596 --> 00:57:57.140
[Sonny] Plan A is called Plan A 'cause
it's when everything is going right.

00:57:57.223 --> 00:57:58.383
You see anything going right?

00:57:58.933 --> 00:58:00.602
Plan C. Softs.

00:58:00.685 --> 00:58:03.813
It's not his call.
Tell him A, as in "asshole."

00:58:04.564 --> 00:58:06.232
Okay, let's go! Turn 'em out! Hard tires.

00:58:06.316 --> 00:58:07.817
[Sonny] Softs, goddamn it.

00:58:13.198 --> 00:58:16.159
-What's wrong with the car?
-The guy sitting in it.

00:58:16.242 --> 00:58:20.955
Are you insane? We need hard tires.
Everybody here is at a one-stop race.

00:58:21.039 --> 00:58:23.124
[Sonny] We do what
everybody does, we lose.

00:58:24.834 --> 00:58:26.377
-Make him go!
-How?

00:58:27.128 --> 00:58:30.131
You think I don't know my tires?
I was a mechanic.

00:58:30.215 --> 00:58:33.927
Five championship titles
with my bare freaking hands!

00:58:36.971 --> 00:58:37.972
Give him his tires.

00:58:38.973 --> 00:58:40.892
-[Hugh] Okay, let's go.
-Go, go, change!

00:58:40.975 --> 00:58:42.602
Let's go, let's go! Change quick, now!

00:58:47.941 --> 00:58:48.942
[Sonny] Be ready.

00:58:49.025 --> 00:58:50.652
Ready for what?

00:58:57.951 --> 00:59:01.037
-Where's JP sitting?
-[Hugh] Currently running P14.

00:59:03.331 --> 00:59:04.791
[Sonny] All right, here we go now.

00:59:05.291 --> 00:59:06.584
[Croft] Hayes makes his move,

00:59:06.668 --> 00:59:09.254
chasing Kevin Magnussen.
It's a late lunge!

00:59:09.337 --> 00:59:10.922
[Brundle] He's damaged his front wing.

00:59:11.005 --> 00:59:15.844
Any driver knows Magnussen will shut
the door on a clumsy move like that.

00:59:15.927 --> 00:59:17.679
[Sonny] Aw, dagnabbit.

00:59:17.762 --> 00:59:19.180
Plan C for "chaos."

00:59:19.264 --> 00:59:20.390
[chuckles]

00:59:20.473 --> 00:59:23.768
[Croft] So that will bring out a
safety car, which always shakes up a race.

00:59:23.852 --> 00:59:26.896
Slows down the leaders,
leaves the field bunched up together,

00:59:26.980 --> 00:59:29.315
and gives teams
the chance for a quick pit stop,

00:59:29.399 --> 00:59:31.734
which only costs half the usual time.

00:59:31.818 --> 00:59:33.278
[Joshua] Safety car. We're boxing, right?

00:59:33.361 --> 00:59:34.612
Standby. Kate,

00:59:34.696 --> 00:59:37.073
shouldn't we take advantage
while the safety car window is open?

00:59:37.156 --> 00:59:39.242
It's early. We gain track position
if we stay out.

00:59:39.325 --> 00:59:42.704
[Rico] Stay out, stay out.
Want you out. Push, push, Joshua.

00:59:42.787 --> 00:59:44.873
[Brundle] So, the midfield moves up
for the moment,

00:59:44.956 --> 00:59:47.292
including Joshua Pearce to P12.

00:59:47.959 --> 00:59:50.211
[Joshua] This guy better not
be messing up my race.

00:59:55.717 --> 00:59:56.718
Where's JP now?

00:59:56.801 --> 00:59:58.261
Currently running P12.

01:00:04.976 --> 01:00:06.936
Okay. Plan C. Be ready.

01:00:07.896 --> 01:00:09.314
He's gonna do it again.

01:00:12.984 --> 01:00:15.320
[Croft] Back marker Hayes
is now down a lap.

01:00:15.403 --> 01:00:18.740
He has to let Bottas pass,
or face a five-second penalty.

01:00:18.823 --> 01:00:21.492
[Brundle] Hayes is making it
very difficult for Bottas.

01:00:21.576 --> 01:00:24.746
Under the rules he has to let him through
before passing three blue flags,

01:00:24.829 --> 01:00:26.497
or risk a penalty.

01:00:26.581 --> 01:00:29.792
Hey, I'm just putting it out there,
but, uh, maybe you should drive.

01:00:31.294 --> 01:00:34.047
[Hugh] Sonny, you've gotten the blue flag.
Let Bottas through.

01:00:34.923 --> 01:00:36.674
[Sonny] Come on, now. Little closer.

01:00:38.635 --> 01:00:40.220
[Hugh] Sonny, do you copy?

01:00:40.303 --> 01:00:42.013
[Sonny] I hear ya. Lettin' him through.

01:00:43.515 --> 01:00:44.849
Whoops, my bad.

01:00:44.933 --> 01:00:46.768
[Croft] And that's his front wing again!

01:00:46.851 --> 01:00:49.729
Oh, that's gonna bring out
another safety car.

01:00:49.812 --> 01:00:52.774
Given that each wing
costs more than £200,000,

01:00:52.857 --> 01:00:55.568
I think the team might want
Sonny to start chipping in there.

01:00:56.194 --> 01:00:57.362
[chuckles]

01:01:00.782 --> 01:01:03.034
[Joshua] Guys, it's another free stop.
Please tell me we're boxing.

01:01:03.117 --> 01:01:04.577
[Rico] Uh, we're checking.

01:01:04.661 --> 01:01:07.205
-Keep him out.
-Stay out. Stay out. You are staying out.

01:01:07.288 --> 01:01:09.541
[Croft] More drivers come in
to take fresh tires,

01:01:09.624 --> 01:01:13.878
but still, Joshua Pearce remains on track.
He's moved up to P11.

01:01:16.714 --> 01:01:18.132
Look who's back.

01:01:21.886 --> 01:01:23.596
I know, I know. Be ready.

01:01:27.225 --> 01:01:28.393
What is he doing?

01:01:30.144 --> 01:01:31.744
I think he's trying to score us a point.

01:01:33.982 --> 01:01:36.192
[Sonny] Tell JP to save his tires.

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:40.029
Joshua, just take care of
your tires, okay?

01:01:40.113 --> 01:01:41.823
You have to make them last.

01:01:41.906 --> 01:01:44.701
[Joshua] Last? No shit. I will be.

01:01:47.829 --> 01:01:50.623
[Brundle] With four laps to go
in this stop-and-go race,

01:01:50.707 --> 01:01:51.875
thanks to Sonny Hayes,

01:01:51.958 --> 01:01:54.711
the driver helped most is his teammate,
now in tenth.

01:01:54.794 --> 01:01:57.714
With a 12-second gap ahead of Stroll.

01:01:58.214 --> 01:02:00.175
Tell JP to maintain that gap.

01:02:00.258 --> 01:02:01.426
Keep pushing.

01:02:02.635 --> 01:02:05.180
[Joshua] My tires are gone, man.
What are you waiting for?

01:02:05.263 --> 01:02:07.056
Copy that. We have to call it.

01:02:07.140 --> 01:02:08.600
He's losing over a second every lap.

01:02:09.309 --> 01:02:10.476
Stand by.

01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:14.314
[Croft] Into turn two. Hayes battles with
the Williams and pushes it wide.

01:02:14.397 --> 01:02:16.274
Seriously, what are we waiting for?

01:02:19.819 --> 01:02:20.862
[Croft] Sonny's off the track.

01:02:20.945 --> 01:02:23.698
He's gone too far over. [groans]

01:02:23.781 --> 01:02:25.158
And that's gonna cause damage.

01:02:25.241 --> 01:02:27.911
-Plan C.
-[laughs]

01:02:28.536 --> 01:02:30.246
Oopsie. Sorry, guys.

01:02:30.330 --> 01:02:34.250
[Croft] That's the third safety car
involving the Apex GP driver,

01:02:34.334 --> 01:02:37.420
bringing the Hungarian Grand Prix
to an absolute crawl.

01:02:37.962 --> 01:02:40.131
A sub three-second stop,
and he'll keep P10.

01:02:40.215 --> 01:02:41.549
Box, Joshua. Box, box, box.

01:02:41.633 --> 01:02:43.176
[Joshua] Copy. Coming in.

01:02:45.595 --> 01:02:46.804
What did you say?

01:02:46.888 --> 01:02:49.349
[Brundle] Joshua Pearce
finally gets to pit.

01:02:49.432 --> 01:02:53.102
[Croft] And with a quick stop here,
he could stay in the top ten.

01:03:00.985 --> 01:03:02.028
[grunts]

01:03:02.111 --> 01:03:04.113
[Brundle] This is critical.

01:03:04.197 --> 01:03:08.535
Pearce must beat Stroll to the
pit exit line to maintain tenth place.

01:03:10.078 --> 01:03:11.371
[Croft] And he's done it!

01:03:11.454 --> 01:03:15.208
With yellow flags out, all the cars
are forced to hold track position,

01:03:15.291 --> 01:03:17.419
-meaning that thanks to Sonny Hayes…
-[Joshua] Let's go!

01:03:17.502 --> 01:03:19.712
-…the race ends under a safety car.
-Yeah!

01:03:19.796 --> 01:03:21.631
-Vegas!
-What? Whoa!

01:03:22.590 --> 01:03:24.884
Hey, yeah. Fuck you. [laughs]

01:03:26.970 --> 01:03:29.305
Yeah! [laughs, grunts]

01:03:29.389 --> 01:03:30.723
Yes, baby!

01:03:30.807 --> 01:03:33.810
[crowd cheering]

01:03:41.734 --> 01:03:43.403
[Joshua chuckles] You're crazy, bro.

01:03:43.486 --> 01:03:46.030
[Sonny] It's just tenth.
What are you smiling about?

01:03:48.366 --> 01:03:50.201
[Croft] And behind our podium placings,

01:03:50.285 --> 01:03:52.871
Hamilton and Piastri
complete the top five,

01:03:52.954 --> 01:03:54.747
-and Joshua Pearce in tenth…
-Wow.

01:03:54.831 --> 01:03:57.458
-…scoring Expensify Apex GP…
-Yeah, baby.

01:03:57.542 --> 01:03:59.127
…their first ever point.

01:04:01.379 --> 01:04:04.007
Did you see me? Crazy, right?

01:04:04.090 --> 01:04:06.926
-[Sonny] A deal's a deal. I finished.
-Yeah, in last place.

01:04:07.010 --> 01:04:08.970
Sounds great when you say it.

01:04:15.143 --> 01:04:17.104
[interviewer] I know you have to go
see the stewards later,

01:04:17.187 --> 01:04:18.772
what do you think they're
gonna make of your race today?

01:04:18.855 --> 01:04:20.940
Well, I have to admit,
you guys got this one right.

01:04:21.024 --> 01:04:23.776
-I'm, like… Thank you. Thank you.
-Good job. Yeah.

01:04:24.319 --> 01:04:27.363
I'm still a bit rusty and, you know,
finding my way with this car,

01:04:27.447 --> 01:04:28.865
but I'm confident we'll get there.

01:04:28.948 --> 01:04:32.827
A rope-a-dope at Silverstone,
a demolition derby here in Hungary…

01:04:32.911 --> 01:04:34.204
You've been banned from casinos.

01:04:34.287 --> 01:04:36.665
Are you trying to get banned from F1?
Take the whole team down with you?

01:04:36.748 --> 01:04:39.042
Tell you what, Don,
what do you say we make a bet?

01:04:39.125 --> 01:04:41.294
Your £10 against my 10 grand.

01:04:41.377 --> 01:04:44.214
We place at Monza, I win your 10.
We don't, you win mine.

01:04:44.297 --> 01:04:45.882
-[scoffs]
-Let's do this, man.

01:04:45.965 --> 01:04:47.365
Put your money where your mouth is.

01:04:48.801 --> 01:04:50.386
What the hell? I'll take that.

01:04:50.470 --> 01:04:52.222
-Thank you.
-Thank you so much.

01:04:52.305 --> 01:04:54.891
Hey. No more press.

01:04:54.974 --> 01:04:57.143
No, Sonny, you don't wanna make
the media your enemy.

01:04:57.227 --> 01:04:58.478
And you'll be fined.

01:04:58.561 --> 01:04:59.687
Take it out of my paycheck.

01:05:00.271 --> 01:05:01.648
We don't pay you enough.

01:05:02.774 --> 01:05:04.234
You know, I have to say.

01:05:05.735 --> 01:05:06.778
I kinda like it.

01:05:08.154 --> 01:05:11.491
It's very sort of punk rock for the brand.

01:05:11.574 --> 01:05:12.825
[Peter sighs]

01:05:14.577 --> 01:05:15.578
[Ruben] Hmm.

01:05:24.379 --> 01:05:25.630
Let's run it again.

01:05:34.097 --> 01:05:35.431
How long's he been in there?

01:05:36.015 --> 01:05:39.602
All day. Playing with different
tire pressures, ride heights.

01:05:40.937 --> 01:05:42.188
What were his times?

01:05:42.689 --> 01:05:43.773
He found half a second.

01:05:49.404 --> 01:05:50.738
Give me the same setup as him.

01:05:51.447 --> 01:05:53.616
[typing]

01:06:12.302 --> 01:06:14.262
It must be late. I'm seeing double.

01:06:14.345 --> 01:06:15.346
[Kate chuckles]

01:06:16.389 --> 01:06:18.850
A deal's a deal.
I'm building her for combat.

01:06:20.393 --> 01:06:21.477
At the Dutch Grand Prix,

01:06:21.561 --> 01:06:25.940
you'll be entering the Tarzan Corner
at 322 kilometers per hour.

01:06:26.024 --> 01:06:28.193
Yeah. Too late to change my mind?

01:06:28.276 --> 01:06:29.903
-Yeah.
-[chuckles]

01:06:36.326 --> 01:06:38.119
To answer your question,

01:06:38.203 --> 01:06:41.873
I was in aerospace at Lockheed
when Ruben came in and…

01:06:42.874 --> 01:06:44.959
He liked my work, liked my attitude,

01:06:45.043 --> 01:06:49.172
and he sold me on the thrill of fighting
to the death for a tenth of a second.

01:06:50.381 --> 01:06:53.718
Traveling the world, the roar of a crowd…

01:06:54.302 --> 01:06:57.347
So, I ran the idea past my husband.

01:06:59.933 --> 01:07:02.727
Who swiftly became my ex-husband.

01:07:05.146 --> 01:07:06.147
Good night.

01:07:07.106 --> 01:07:08.107
Good night.

01:07:30.797 --> 01:07:33.132
[line ringing]

01:07:33.216 --> 01:07:34.717
[Ruben] Do you know what time it is?

01:07:35.552 --> 01:07:36.845
All right.

01:07:36.928 --> 01:07:38.429
Tell me about the kid.

01:07:45.270 --> 01:07:47.146
Okay, here's another one my dad would say.

01:07:47.230 --> 01:07:49.357
"Slow is smooth, smooth is fast."

01:07:50.275 --> 01:07:52.652
For what it's worth. One more time around?

01:07:52.735 --> 01:07:55.822
-Just one? Come on. Is that all?
-[Sonny chuckles]

01:07:55.905 --> 01:07:57.407
-[grunts]
-I'd never live with myself,

01:07:57.490 --> 01:07:59.909
if I can't keep up with you, Mr. 1990s.

01:07:59.993 --> 01:08:01.536
-[chuckles]
-Let's go!

01:08:02.078 --> 01:08:04.414
Joining us today,
we have Kaspar Smolinski,

01:08:04.497 --> 01:08:06.624
Zak Brown and Fred Vasseur.

01:08:06.708 --> 01:08:10.128
Now, Kaspar, can we start with you,
after what was a fantastic result

01:08:10.211 --> 01:08:12.547
-for the team in Hungary last time out…
-Thank you.

01:08:12.630 --> 01:08:17.844
…but Sonny has got you skirting the line
of penalties and violations.

01:08:17.927 --> 01:08:20.137
Is this your only strategy,

01:08:20.220 --> 01:08:23.140
and have you got any spare parts left
in the factory?

01:08:23.224 --> 01:08:24.725
[audience chuckling]

01:08:24.809 --> 01:08:26.185
We compete like everybody else.

01:08:26.269 --> 01:08:27.604
Race models change.

01:08:27.687 --> 01:08:29.272
We must adapt, huh?

01:08:29.856 --> 01:08:31.399
Well, Zak, can we bring you in on this?

01:08:31.482 --> 01:08:36.613
Because you've faced Hayes before,
you know the gray areas in which he works.

01:08:37.363 --> 01:08:40.575
Certainly do. Uh, first of all,
he's a lot grayer now.

01:08:40.658 --> 01:08:42.660
-[audience chuckles]
-And, uh, we keep tabs on him,

01:08:42.743 --> 01:08:44.037
you know, back there behind us.

01:08:44.120 --> 01:08:47.207
-[audience chuckles]
-And Fred, any concerns from Ferrari?

01:08:47.290 --> 01:08:49.375
What does Ferrari think of Apex?

01:08:50.126 --> 01:08:53.171
-We don't.
-[audience chuckling]

01:08:53.254 --> 01:08:55.173
["Hold Me" playing]

01:09:07.185 --> 01:09:12.106
[fans clamoring] Sonny! You're the best!

01:09:14.108 --> 01:09:16.944
[Kate] A better qualifying yesterday
gets us in the thick of things.

01:09:17.028 --> 01:09:19.488
P10, P15. [inhales sharply]

01:09:19.572 --> 01:09:21.282
So we're gonna go for a two stop.

01:09:21.366 --> 01:09:26.162
Medium-hard-medium, that's plan A.
Final stint, we go hards for plan B.

01:09:26.246 --> 01:09:28.539
So, on this,
do you have any track concerns?

01:09:28.622 --> 01:09:30.625
Don't look at me. Look at him.

01:09:32.417 --> 01:09:33.670
It's good for JP.

01:09:34.212 --> 01:09:35.212
Start me on hards.

01:09:36.089 --> 01:09:38.800
Nah, the track's cooled down.
You won't have any grip.

01:09:38.883 --> 01:09:40.176
That's right.

01:09:40.844 --> 01:09:43.595
For three weeks,
all the talk's been how reckless I am.

01:09:44.180 --> 01:09:46.765
Everyone's wondering
if I'm gonna drive 'em off track,

01:09:46.850 --> 01:09:49.310
which means no one's
gonna be watching out for him.

01:09:51.437 --> 01:09:54.983
Today, you win us this race.

01:10:02.282 --> 01:10:05.618
[Croft] Twenty laps down here at Monza,
and the pack have been split.

01:10:05.702 --> 01:10:08.413
The leaders are pulling away,
led by Max Verstappen,

01:10:08.496 --> 01:10:10.957
with Joshua Pearce back in P10.

01:10:11.040 --> 01:10:13.751
[Brundle] Meanwhile, Sonny Hayes
is holding up the rest of the pack,

01:10:13.835 --> 01:10:16.171
stuck behind him in a DRS train.

01:10:17.130 --> 01:10:20.800
[Croft] Pearce looks to be in
a great position to finish in the top ten,

01:10:20.884 --> 01:10:23.803
and maybe even a run to the podium.

01:10:25.889 --> 01:10:28.058
[Brundle] But there's still a long way
to go in this race,

01:10:28.141 --> 01:10:32.103
and with rain potentially forecast,
anything can happen.

01:10:32.687 --> 01:10:34.063
Tires are gone. Coming in.

01:10:34.147 --> 01:10:35.481
Yeah, copy. Box. Box.

01:10:36.065 --> 01:10:38.568
[Croft] Apex GP is prepping
a fresh set of tires for Hayes.

01:10:38.651 --> 01:10:42.405
That's gonna bring in
all the other teams to avoid the undercut.

01:10:42.488 --> 01:10:44.073
Uh, changed my mind.

01:10:44.157 --> 01:10:47.702
[Croft] But, no! He's staying out,
with the cars behind him all scrambling

01:10:47.785 --> 01:10:52.248
to get on fresh tires that apparently
he doesn't think he needs anymore.

01:10:52.332 --> 01:10:54.834
Should we just do the opposite
of what he tells us to do?

01:10:54.918 --> 01:10:56.878
Stand by till I lose my tires.

01:10:57.921 --> 01:11:01.007
-I thought he had lost his tires.
-[stammers] I think he means literally.

01:11:03.968 --> 01:11:05.970
Puncture, left rear. Coming in.

01:11:06.054 --> 01:11:08.014
[Croft] And there goes Hayes's tires.

01:11:08.097 --> 01:11:10.517
[Brundle] That's quite a mess,
gravel on the track.

01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:13.978
That will bring out the virtual safety car
for a quick sweep.

01:11:14.062 --> 01:11:15.522
[Croft] So the race gets neutralized.

01:11:15.605 --> 01:11:19.317
Everyone slows down
to 40% of their racing speed,

01:11:19.400 --> 01:11:21.402
and all the race strategies
will get a reset.

01:11:21.486 --> 01:11:24.531
[Brundle] And that is why this is
the perfect time to take a pit stop.

01:11:24.614 --> 01:11:25.990
While you're in the pit lane,

01:11:26.074 --> 01:11:29.118
your opponents
are restricted to a much slower pace

01:11:29.202 --> 01:11:31.913
and you're not going to lose
as much track position when you rejoin.

01:11:31.996 --> 01:11:35.250
-I take it I'm staying out, right?
-Copy. Joshua, stay out. Stay out.

01:11:35.333 --> 01:11:38.002
-We want you out to gain track position.
-Copy.

01:11:38.086 --> 01:11:40.088
Up is down, down is up.

01:11:47.053 --> 01:11:50.306
[Croft] Sonny Hayes hesitated
before he left his pit box,

01:11:50.390 --> 01:11:53.226
and he's come out just in front
of Max Verstappen.

01:11:53.309 --> 01:11:54.561
[Max] That was naughty.

01:11:54.644 --> 01:11:56.855
[Brundle] Hayes has slowed a bit
in the pit lane,

01:11:56.938 --> 01:12:00.900
which will cost the Red Bull
and the two Ferraris precious time.

01:12:00.984 --> 01:12:02.193
Push, Joshua. Push.

01:12:02.277 --> 01:12:03.820
You are now P4. P4.

01:12:03.903 --> 01:12:08.199
[Croft] Who's coming up from behind?
Here he is, Joshua Pearce.

01:12:08.283 --> 01:12:10.076
-Let's see! Let's go!
-Yes!

01:12:10.159 --> 01:12:11.787
-This is all playing into his hands…
-Wow.

01:12:11.870 --> 01:12:14.247
…at the moment.
Could be a dream afternoon.

01:12:14.330 --> 01:12:17.208
But can Hayes hold Verstappen
for a little bit longer?

01:12:17.292 --> 01:12:20.336
Verstappen tries into turn one,
nothing doing there.

01:12:20.420 --> 01:12:23.214
Gets the better exit.
Through the Curva Grande we go.

01:12:23.298 --> 01:12:25.550
-Damn, he's good.
-Verstappen's trying to get past.

01:12:25.633 --> 01:12:27.594
[Brundle] Sonny Hayes
looking carefully in his mirrors.

01:12:27.677 --> 01:12:29.929
He must let Max Verstappen through.

01:12:30.013 --> 01:12:31.639
Yeah, I deserved that.

01:12:31.723 --> 01:12:34.017
[Brundle] And Max shows his disapproval,

01:12:34.100 --> 01:12:37.770
and I don't blame him, as they head down
towards the second chicane.

01:12:37.854 --> 01:12:40.481
[Croft]
And through goes Joshua Pearce in P4,

01:12:40.565 --> 01:12:43.193
now much closer to the front of the pack.

01:12:43.276 --> 01:12:44.277
[thunder rumbles]

01:12:46.112 --> 01:12:48.907
[Brundle] Just seven laps to go,
and here comes the rain.

01:12:48.990 --> 01:12:52.118
[Croft] Let's see who plays it safe
with a switch to the intermediate tire,

01:12:52.202 --> 01:12:54.746
and who might gamble
to stay out on slicks.

01:13:01.169 --> 01:13:02.963
It's getting tricky out here, guys.
What's the plan?

01:13:03.046 --> 01:13:06.966
You're running P4. We think P2 and P3
are switching to inters for safety,

01:13:07.050 --> 01:13:08.760
and it looks like P1 is staying out.

01:13:08.843 --> 01:13:10.723
-What do you wanna do?
-What's Sonny gonna do?

01:13:11.471 --> 01:13:12.889
Take a wild guess.

01:13:12.972 --> 01:13:14.532
-[Joshua] I'm staying out.
-Copy that.

01:13:15.600 --> 01:13:18.978
[Brundle] And the two Ferraris
come in for intermediate tires.

01:13:19.062 --> 01:13:21.439
Let's see who else
decides to play it safe.

01:13:21.523 --> 01:13:25.485
[Croft] And as George Russell pits,
Joshua Pearce moves into P2.

01:13:25.568 --> 01:13:27.111
[cheering]

01:13:27.195 --> 01:13:29.656
Sonny, Joshua is staying out on slicks.
If he can hold on and find a dry line,

01:13:29.739 --> 01:13:30.823
he's gonna finish second.

01:13:30.907 --> 01:13:31.950
Second's not enough.

01:13:33.326 --> 01:13:34.452
Damn it.

01:13:34.994 --> 01:13:36.704
Okay, coming in for inters.

01:13:36.788 --> 01:13:39.415
-Inters, inters.
-Let's go! He's coming in!

01:13:45.922 --> 01:13:48.299
-How far behind me are they?
-Thirty seconds.

01:13:48.842 --> 01:13:50.718
Oh, my God.
He's gonna take out Verstappen.

01:13:50.802 --> 01:13:52.554
Let me know
when they hit the main straight.

01:13:52.637 --> 01:13:56.057
Don't tell him! They penalize both cars.
They will take the win away.

01:13:56.140 --> 01:13:57.141
Just trust me, will ya?

01:13:59.644 --> 01:14:01.646
I'm pushing but I can't catch him.

01:14:01.729 --> 01:14:03.732
[Brundle] As the race leaders
approach the main straight,

01:14:03.815 --> 01:14:07.110
Sonny Hayes is in another standoff
over team strategy.

01:14:07.193 --> 01:14:08.695
-Now.
-No!

01:14:09.946 --> 01:14:12.574
[Croft] Finally,
Hayes back out onto the track,

01:14:12.657 --> 01:14:14.409
and just in front of Verstappen.

01:14:14.492 --> 01:14:17.537
Now he'll get a blue flag here
so Verstappen can get past,

01:14:17.620 --> 01:14:22.041
but until then, the Dutch driver
is caught up in Hayes's dirty air.

01:14:22.125 --> 01:14:24.043
[Brundle] With every turn he hangs on,

01:14:24.127 --> 01:14:26.629
he slows Verstappen
a fraction of a second,

01:14:26.713 --> 01:14:30.133
providing Joshua Pearce
one last chance to catch up.

01:14:30.216 --> 01:14:31.496
I can see him. I'm almost there.

01:14:33.344 --> 01:14:34.345
Tell JP to follow me.

01:14:34.429 --> 01:14:38.433
-Copy. Uh, Joshua, Sonny is your tow.
-I'm right behind him.

01:14:39.601 --> 01:14:41.227
[Croft] Verstappen pulls away then.

01:14:41.311 --> 01:14:44.105
But now, onto the rear wing
of his teammate's car

01:14:44.189 --> 01:14:45.523
comes Joshua Pearce.

01:14:45.607 --> 01:14:48.026
[Brundle] Pearce picks up
the slipstream from Hayes,

01:14:48.109 --> 01:14:51.196
gaining time,
but driving blind in the spray.

01:14:53.865 --> 01:14:55.992
Come on. Stay with me. Stay with me now.

01:15:02.582 --> 01:15:03.750
Pass. Pass.

01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:05.293
-Overtake him. Overtake.
-Copy.

01:15:05.376 --> 01:15:10.131
[Croft] He's been gaining, and boom!
Joshua Pearce slingshots past Sonny Hayes,

01:15:10.215 --> 01:15:13.301
-and now is in striking distance of P1.
-[cheering]

01:15:13.384 --> 01:15:15.845
Tell JP to wait for the straight
into turn one.

01:15:15.929 --> 01:15:17.305
Be patient.

01:15:17.388 --> 01:15:19.516
-Straight at turn one.
-[crew member] Copy.

01:15:19.599 --> 01:15:23.853
Joshua, Sonny says wait for the straight.
The straight into turn one.

01:15:25.355 --> 01:15:27.148
[Joshua] I'm right there.

01:15:27.232 --> 01:15:28.441
I've got him.

01:15:29.317 --> 01:15:31.736
[Brundle] Pearce is right on the gearbox
of Verstappen,

01:15:31.819 --> 01:15:34.656
down the back straight
at over 200 miles an hour.

01:15:34.739 --> 01:15:36.157
I see an opening. Going for it.

01:15:36.783 --> 01:15:38.868
[Brundle] The rookie attacks in 11.

01:15:39.369 --> 01:15:40.370
No, no!

01:15:41.829 --> 01:15:43.540
[Croft]
Pearce pulls alongside the Red Bull,

01:15:43.623 --> 01:15:46.334
he's wheels ahead,
for the first time ever…

01:15:46.417 --> 01:15:49.337
Apex GP… Oh, no!

01:15:49.420 --> 01:15:50.797
No!

01:16:09.607 --> 01:16:12.068
-[sad music playing]
-[no audible dialogue]

01:17:05.205 --> 01:17:10.001
[monitor beeping]

01:17:18.301 --> 01:17:20.637
[reporter speaking Italian on television]

01:17:23.765 --> 01:17:24.807
[sighs]

01:17:26.726 --> 01:17:28.645
[sighs, in English] For God's sake.

01:17:37.946 --> 01:17:40.573
-[Ruben] Bernadette, how's he doing?
-[Bernadette grunts]

01:17:40.657 --> 01:17:41.908
He's stable.

01:17:41.991 --> 01:17:43.660
He's resting now.

01:17:44.661 --> 01:17:46.412
[exhales heavily, mutters]

01:17:47.038 --> 01:17:48.623
Very happy to hear it.

01:17:48.706 --> 01:17:51.209
I'm so sorry for what happened.
It was clearly...

01:17:51.292 --> 01:17:53.461
Sonny, over here, please.

01:18:00.051 --> 01:18:01.511
[sighing]

01:18:07.976 --> 01:18:10.812
Um, I just wanna say I've been...

01:18:10.895 --> 01:18:12.480
Joshua says you're an asshole.

01:18:15.108 --> 01:18:16.609
Yeah, that tracks.

01:18:16.693 --> 01:18:19.070
I think you're a dangerous asshole.

01:18:21.030 --> 01:18:23.658
-Ms. Pearce...
-You're part of the same team, right?

01:18:23.741 --> 01:18:24.951
Looking out for each other.

01:18:25.034 --> 01:18:27.745
Except you had him
doing something so dangerous

01:18:27.829 --> 01:18:29.998
it almost got him killed.

01:18:31.457 --> 01:18:34.502
-Okay, listen...
-No, you listen to me.

01:18:35.336 --> 01:18:37.255
This is my son.

01:18:38.381 --> 01:18:40.633
And if anything…
anything else happens to him,

01:18:40.717 --> 01:18:42.051
I'm coming after you.

01:18:42.135 --> 01:18:44.721
And you better pray I don't put you
in a bed next to Joshua

01:18:44.804 --> 01:18:46.848
for a very, very long time.

01:18:47.599 --> 01:18:48.600
Clear?

01:18:51.060 --> 01:18:52.395
Sure.

01:18:56.399 --> 01:18:57.901
[sighs]

01:19:06.201 --> 01:19:08.995
[reporters murmuring, clamoring]

01:19:09.829 --> 01:19:10.955
Sonny, Sonny.

01:19:11.039 --> 01:19:13.917
Do you think Joshua blames you
for what happened in Monza?

01:19:17.629 --> 01:19:20.590
-[reporters clamoring]
-[reporter] Sonny, come on.

01:19:20.673 --> 01:19:22.967
It was clear
that you were running his race.

01:19:23.051 --> 01:19:26.596
Look, you kept him out on slick tires,
in dangerous conditions,

01:19:26.679 --> 01:19:30.350
that even if you told him not to pass,
wasn't the accident inevitable?

01:19:30.433 --> 01:19:32.477
-If I may. If I may.
-[reporters clamoring]

01:19:32.560 --> 01:19:34.604
Joshua's back home, recovering.

01:19:34.687 --> 01:19:36.856
We are expecting his return
in a few weeks.

01:19:36.940 --> 01:19:42.779
Until that moment, our reserve driver,
Luca Cortez right there, will drive and…

01:19:42.862 --> 01:19:45.448
-Next man up.
-[clamoring] Answer the question!

01:19:47.825 --> 01:19:50.912
[Buxton] A chaotic week
for Expensify Apex GP,

01:19:50.995 --> 01:19:53.873
and again, it's Sonny Hayes at the center.

01:19:53.957 --> 01:19:57.627
Many are blaming him for his teammate's
horrific accident at Monza.

01:19:57.710 --> 01:20:02.215
His high-stakes, gambling style of racing
has the whole grid on edge,

01:20:02.298 --> 01:20:06.135
and while the controversy continues
over who was to blame,

01:20:06.219 --> 01:20:09.722
doctors have said that Pearce
will miss the next three races,

01:20:09.806 --> 01:20:14.143
due to the burns suffered on his hands
as he begins his road to recovery.

01:20:21.651 --> 01:20:24.028
[Kate] Today, we're going
with our combat upgrade.

01:20:24.696 --> 01:20:28.116
The revised shapes will improve
the flow field under the floor,

01:20:28.199 --> 01:20:32.078
allowing us to run in dirty air
with minimal loss of performance.

01:20:32.161 --> 01:20:34.873
Means we have to keep the field close
at all times,

01:20:35.373 --> 01:20:38.710
and as for this week's plan C…

01:20:44.757 --> 01:20:48.469
They've docked us to the back of the grid
'cause they don't like the way we drive.

01:20:48.553 --> 01:20:50.513
Fine. Fuck 'em.

01:20:51.431 --> 01:20:54.642
'Cause if we can pick up
a tenth of a second from you,

01:20:54.726 --> 01:20:58.396
and from you, and you, and me…

01:20:58.479 --> 01:21:01.191
If everyone in this room
can make one critical contribution,

01:21:01.274 --> 01:21:02.567
that's a second every lap.

01:21:03.276 --> 01:21:07.822
And after 72 laps, that's the difference
between last and first.

01:21:09.866 --> 01:21:10.992
Plan C…

01:21:12.619 --> 01:21:14.287
Plan C's for combat.

01:21:16.789 --> 01:21:21.628
Combat, combat, combat.

01:21:21.711 --> 01:21:27.425
[crew chanting] Combat, combat,
combat, combat.

01:21:27.509 --> 01:21:29.135
[chanting continues]

01:21:29.219 --> 01:21:30.387
[driving electronic song playing]

01:21:30.470 --> 01:21:34.474
♪ I don't wanna lose my mind
I don't wanna lose myself ♪

01:21:34.557 --> 01:21:38.853
♪ Tell me if I crossed a line
I ain't trying to hurt myself ♪

01:21:38.937 --> 01:21:44.067
♪ Didn't want to call your name
Only got myself to blame ♪

01:21:44.150 --> 01:21:45.818
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

01:21:45.902 --> 01:21:48.071
♪ In my world, in my mind
Always running out of time ♪

01:21:48.154 --> 01:21:49.239
[crowd cheering]

01:21:49.322 --> 01:21:51.407
[Croft] And that's Hayes
in the upgraded Apex.

01:21:51.491 --> 01:21:54.827
Now the team were penalized
back to last place after Monza,

01:21:54.911 --> 01:21:59.165
but here he is, coming from the cellar,
passing his new teammate, Luca Cortez.

01:21:59.249 --> 01:22:01.626
♪ …still I wait for you ♪

01:22:01.709 --> 01:22:03.211
[vocalizes]

01:22:03.294 --> 01:22:04.754
♪ Yeah, it feels… ♪

01:22:04.838 --> 01:22:07.715
[Croft] Round the banking,
Hayes has got past Ocon.

01:22:07.799 --> 01:22:11.553
This is brilliant last lap drama.
What a fantastic finish.

01:22:11.636 --> 01:22:13.137
[laughs]

01:22:14.931 --> 01:22:16.474
[exclaims, chuckles]

01:22:16.558 --> 01:22:21.479
♪ Ain't no way to tell
Which way it's gonna go ♪

01:22:21.563 --> 01:22:25.024
♪ But it feels ♪

01:22:25.108 --> 01:22:28.987
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:22:29.070 --> 01:22:33.241
♪ No question if it's wrong or right ♪

01:22:33.825 --> 01:22:37.495
♪ And now it's too late
No way to take it slow ♪

01:22:48.047 --> 01:22:50.508
[Brundle] Another fearless attack
from Hayes.

01:22:50.592 --> 01:22:53.428
And here's where the Apex GP
has found strength.

01:22:53.511 --> 01:22:56.681
Three-tenths gained every lap,
and in the corners alone.

01:22:57.348 --> 01:23:00.685
♪ I don't wanna lose my mind
I don't wanna lose myself ♪

01:23:00.768 --> 01:23:02.562
[Croft] Scrapping away on the last lap,

01:23:02.645 --> 01:23:05.899
Sonny Hayes gets the inside line,
but he can't quite get past.

01:23:05.982 --> 01:23:08.610
George Russell will hang on here
for sixth place,

01:23:08.693 --> 01:23:11.988
but this is Apex GP's best ever finish.

01:23:12.071 --> 01:23:15.450
-It's a valiant seventh.
-Combat, I love it!

01:23:15.533 --> 01:23:18.494
[crowd cheering]

01:23:18.578 --> 01:23:20.618
[manager] Every race you miss,
fans just forget you.

01:23:21.039 --> 01:23:23.291
Sonny always seems to be one step ahead.

01:23:24.709 --> 01:23:28.338
You never know.
Sonny may be a saboteur, Josh.

01:23:28.421 --> 01:23:29.506
He may be a saboteur.

01:23:29.589 --> 01:23:31.299
-[crowd cheering]
-[song continues]

01:23:31.382 --> 01:23:34.469
♪ Yeah it feels ♪

01:23:34.552 --> 01:23:38.848
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:23:38.932 --> 01:23:41.518
♪ No question if it's wrong or right ♪

01:23:41.601 --> 01:23:44.103
[Croft] …and they go wheel to wheel,
Verstappen and Leclerc.

01:23:44.187 --> 01:23:47.398
Verstappen will have the inside.
Perez goes round the outside.

01:23:47.482 --> 01:23:49.817
Perez makes contact with Charles Leclerc

01:23:49.901 --> 01:23:54.364
as Sonny Hayes threads that Apex GP car
through the midfield.

01:24:05.416 --> 01:24:06.709
♪ Yeah ♪

01:24:06.793 --> 01:24:08.628
♪ Bounce back
When the bottles is on me ♪

01:24:08.711 --> 01:24:11.005
♪ I'm pushin' a new pen
Rewriting the story ♪

01:24:11.089 --> 01:24:13.091
♪ Hello to my old ways
Goodbye to the nosebleeds ♪

01:24:13.174 --> 01:24:15.885
♪ You fighting to stay here
You probably OD'ing ♪

01:24:15.969 --> 01:24:18.054
♪ Ain't finna pop for no reason ♪

01:24:18.137 --> 01:24:19.973
♪ I don't throw shots, I run legions ♪

01:24:20.056 --> 01:24:21.683
♪ I been goin' over the top
Where no queen been ♪

01:24:21.766 --> 01:24:23.685
♪ Die with with no regrets
This is my season ♪

01:24:23.768 --> 01:24:25.436
[Croft] Talk about leaving it late.

01:24:25.520 --> 01:24:29.399
Hayes squeezes through on the inside,
and with a run to the line now,

01:24:29.482 --> 01:24:32.402
for their best position ever, P5.

01:24:32.485 --> 01:24:34.404
[Brundle] Give the design team a bonus,

01:24:34.487 --> 01:24:37.156
because the upgrade
has completely changed this car.

01:24:37.240 --> 01:24:39.409
[Croft] And if Joshua Pearce is watching,

01:24:39.492 --> 01:24:42.412
well, he must be thinking,
"What might have been?"

01:24:42.495 --> 01:24:44.372
♪ Yeah, it feels ♪

01:24:44.455 --> 01:24:47.917
♪ So good I might just lose my mind ♪

01:24:48.001 --> 01:24:50.044
He's treating you like a pawn, Josh.

01:24:50.128 --> 01:24:53.798
-Be a knight! Be a knight! Be a knight!
-[bicycle bell ringing]

01:24:57.802 --> 01:24:59.679
[Croft]
Who would have believed this weeks ago?

01:24:59.762 --> 01:25:03.725
Expensify Apex GP
has the racing world on notice.

01:25:03.808 --> 01:25:06.728
[crowd chanting] Apex! Apex! Apex!

01:25:06.811 --> 01:25:09.230
[chanting continues]

01:25:11.399 --> 01:25:16.905
[Brundle] Someone call the 1990s.
Sonny Hayes, if you missed him, he's back.

01:25:16.988 --> 01:25:19.157
[song ends]

01:25:24.037 --> 01:25:26.623
Last one up buys breakfast. [chuckles]

01:25:27.332 --> 01:25:29.876
[indistinct chattering]

01:25:34.672 --> 01:25:35.757
Look who's back.

01:25:36.633 --> 01:25:40.887
[crew cheering, applauding]

01:25:42.347 --> 01:25:43.389
Hello.

01:25:50.438 --> 01:25:52.106
Good to have you back, JP. We missed you.

01:25:53.316 --> 01:25:55.318
[dramatic rap song playing]

01:26:03.576 --> 01:26:08.039
♪ This for the underdogs
This for the underdogs, underdogs ♪

01:26:08.122 --> 01:26:11.918
♪ Slide out the garage
I got a hundred cars ♪

01:26:12.001 --> 01:26:14.087
♪ This for the underdogs ♪

01:26:14.170 --> 01:26:16.172
♪ The teller just ask me
How I want the cashy ♪

01:26:16.256 --> 01:26:17.758
[crowd chanting] Apex! Apex! Apex! Apex!

01:26:17.841 --> 01:26:19.384
♪ I told 'em a hundred large ♪

01:26:19.467 --> 01:26:22.178
♪ I want them gold wraps
Put it up double R ♪

01:26:23.304 --> 01:26:26.766
♪ Tell 'em get out the way
4x4 big Phantom, supe ♪

01:26:26.850 --> 01:26:30.270
♪ They thought I was canceled
I piped up and flipped the channel ♪

01:26:36.943 --> 01:26:39.612
[Croft] It's lights out and away we go!

01:26:39.696 --> 01:26:41.197
And it's a decent start,

01:26:41.281 --> 01:26:44.242
and everyone keeping it clean
as into La Source we go.

01:26:44.325 --> 01:26:45.827
Ferrari ahead of Red Bull,

01:26:45.910 --> 01:26:51.416
but here the two Apex GP cars
looking to work together as a team.

01:26:51.499 --> 01:26:54.627
It's a welcome back to the track
for Joshua Pearce,

01:26:54.711 --> 01:26:56.337
and Sonny Hayes glad to see him,

01:26:56.421 --> 01:27:00.049
as they slice their way
through positions four and five.

01:27:00.133 --> 01:27:02.093
And onto the Kemmel Straight we go.

01:27:02.802 --> 01:27:07.265
Now approaching top speed,
Sonny Hayes ahead of Joshua Pearce.

01:27:07.348 --> 01:27:10.852
He's showing no ill effects
from that time off after the crash.

01:27:10.935 --> 01:27:14.480
The car's working beautifully.
They're working as a team.

01:27:14.564 --> 01:27:18.401
But hang on, Pearce right on his tail,
using the slipstream.

01:27:18.484 --> 01:27:20.820
Is he about to try and overtake?

01:27:20.904 --> 01:27:23.656
Into the chicane we go
and they touch wheels!

01:27:23.740 --> 01:27:25.658
-This is disaster for Apex…
-[exclaiming]

01:27:25.742 --> 01:27:29.495
…as out goes Sonny Hayes
and into the gravel!

01:27:30.955 --> 01:27:32.248
Assholes! [grunts]

01:27:32.832 --> 01:27:35.376
[Brundle]
What is happening with this team?

01:27:35.460 --> 01:27:39.714
Their first race back together,
and they've run into each other.

01:27:41.841 --> 01:27:42.884
-You did great, Joshua.
-Well done, mate.

01:27:42.967 --> 01:27:44.385
[laughs]

01:27:44.469 --> 01:27:45.720
Whoo! [grunts]

01:27:46.262 --> 01:27:48.556
You pull that shit again,
I will knock your teeth out.

01:27:48.640 --> 01:27:50.392
Oh, no one gets past us
without a fight, right?

01:27:50.475 --> 01:27:52.561
Oh, is this funny?
You think you got a seat next year?

01:27:52.644 --> 01:27:54.687
'Cause you just cut your chances in half.

01:27:54.771 --> 01:27:57.148
-That's how dumb you are.
-You failed. You failed!

01:27:57.232 --> 01:27:59.112
-Why should I listen to you anyway, man?
-Hey.

01:27:59.943 --> 01:28:01.069
[exhales heavily]

01:28:01.152 --> 01:28:03.780
Look, man.
I don't give two shits about you.

01:28:03.863 --> 01:28:06.115
You wanna sabotage your career,
you go right ahead.

01:28:06.199 --> 01:28:08.535
I've seen hundreds of guys
with your talent come and go.

01:28:08.618 --> 01:28:10.078
No one cares!

01:28:10.954 --> 01:28:14.624
But you sabotage Ruben, who backed you?
You sabotage his team?

01:28:16.042 --> 01:28:17.210
I won't let you do it.

01:28:22.423 --> 01:28:25.927
-Thanks, coach. [laughs]
-Get your shit together!

01:28:26.010 --> 01:28:28.680
So stupid! God…

01:28:36.813 --> 01:28:38.273
[interviewer]
How would you sum up your race today?

01:28:38.356 --> 01:28:41.234
Ooh. Um, it was good.

01:28:41.317 --> 01:28:44.487
You know, the car feels great.
I think the team's done an amazing job.

01:28:45.196 --> 01:28:47.282
It's just a shame
about the contact with Sonny.

01:28:48.366 --> 01:28:49.659
You hate to see that happen.

01:28:59.586 --> 01:29:01.212
[pants]

01:29:12.724 --> 01:29:13.892
[sighs]

01:29:17.228 --> 01:29:18.980
-[Joshua] Hey, how are you doing?
-[host] Hi, how are you?

01:29:19.063 --> 01:29:20.523
Good. Sensational.

01:29:22.901 --> 01:29:24.944
-Where's the team?
-Right this way, gentlemen.

01:29:25.570 --> 01:29:26.821
[sighs]

01:29:35.705 --> 01:29:38.625
Brilliant, you made it. Come on. Sit down.

01:29:40.793 --> 01:29:42.545
Sonny, you know Joshua.

01:29:42.629 --> 01:29:44.464
Joshua, Sonny.

01:29:45.048 --> 01:29:46.967
So I'm sure you both
have heard the rumors. [sighs]

01:29:47.050 --> 01:29:50.011
We all lose our jobs
if you can't pull off a miracle,

01:29:50.094 --> 01:29:52.139
and that's starting with
staying on the bloody track.

01:29:52.222 --> 01:29:54.265
Well, we were doing just fine
while JP was out.

01:29:54.349 --> 01:29:55.684
I was out because I was listening to you.

01:29:55.767 --> 01:29:57.185
-Ish.
-And please don't call me JP.

01:29:57.268 --> 01:29:58.812
It's a nickname. You don't get to choose.

01:29:58.895 --> 01:30:01.231
And your name doesn't even make sense.
Is it Sonny, is it Hayesie?

01:30:01.314 --> 01:30:02.399
-We don't know, do we, Kate?
-[scoffs]

01:30:02.482 --> 01:30:03.522
-[chuckles]
-[Kate] Lads.

01:30:03.983 --> 01:30:05.318
Have I not delivered you a car?

01:30:08.488 --> 01:30:10.448
So you can do one thing for me.

01:30:10.532 --> 01:30:11.741
Cards.

01:30:12.408 --> 01:30:14.244
Come on. I know you have 'em with ya.

01:30:15.286 --> 01:30:17.205
It's my team meeting,
we're gonna do it my way.

01:30:17.288 --> 01:30:19.166
-We're playing poker.
-[Joshua scoffs] Come on.

01:30:19.249 --> 01:30:21.960
Yeah. Whoever wins gets to be
our number one driver tomorrow,

01:30:22.043 --> 01:30:24.003
and if I win, I get to choose.

01:30:26.089 --> 01:30:28.007
-Didn't he gamble for a living?
-Mm-hmm, yeah.

01:30:28.091 --> 01:30:29.467
Now he's living in a van.

01:30:29.551 --> 01:30:30.802
[chuckles]

01:30:31.511 --> 01:30:32.512
Texas Hold'em?

01:30:35.265 --> 01:30:36.850
["Just Cool" playing]

01:30:41.145 --> 01:30:43.231
[Sonny speaks indistinctly]

01:30:46.901 --> 01:30:49.195
So, Sonny here likes straight talk.

01:30:49.279 --> 01:30:50.864
-[chuckles]
-Isn't that right, Sonny?

01:30:50.947 --> 01:30:53.200
-[Sonny] Yeah, that's what I hear.
-[Kate] So, let's talk.

01:30:53.283 --> 01:30:54.367
Who wants to go first?

01:30:54.450 --> 01:30:56.160
-I'll go first.
-I'll go first.

01:30:56.244 --> 01:30:57.829
No, I'll go first.

01:30:57.912 --> 01:31:01.249
What's the difference between
Joshua Pearce and Sonny Hayes?

01:31:01.332 --> 01:31:02.333
A lot of decades.

01:31:02.417 --> 01:31:04.711
-Hard-won experience.
-Of living in a van?

01:31:04.794 --> 01:31:06.004
Total freedom.

01:31:06.087 --> 01:31:07.130
Total failure.

01:31:07.839 --> 01:31:09.508
Says the guy who still lives with his mom.

01:31:09.591 --> 01:31:11.009
Says the guy with two pair.

01:31:11.092 --> 01:31:14.012
-Says the guy with trips.
-Says the guy with a full house.

01:31:16.264 --> 01:31:18.057
-Girl.
-[Joshua scoffs]

01:31:18.141 --> 01:31:19.893
Wait, I don't even live with my mum.

01:31:19.976 --> 01:31:20.977
Okay.

01:31:21.561 --> 01:31:23.062
She just cooks for me sometimes.

01:31:23.146 --> 01:31:24.397
Mm-hmm.

01:31:26.316 --> 01:31:29.068
If you'd any constructive criticism
for each other, what would it be?

01:31:29.152 --> 01:31:31.352
-Don't be such an arsehole.
-Don't be such a dickhead.

01:31:32.947 --> 01:31:33.948
That was constructive.

01:31:34.032 --> 01:31:35.241
[scoffs]

01:31:36.868 --> 01:31:39.329
You have a deficient frontal cortex.

01:31:41.039 --> 01:31:42.916
-A what?
-You can't analyze risk.

01:31:42.999 --> 01:31:46.377
It's not all your fault.
It's not fully formed yet at your age.

01:31:46.461 --> 01:31:48.046
But come the day you learn patience,

01:31:48.129 --> 01:31:50.215
-and stop being so immature, thinking...
-Patience.

01:31:50.798 --> 01:31:52.318
-Patience is good.
-[Sonny] Patience.

01:31:53.301 --> 01:31:54.552
Joshua.

01:31:55.803 --> 01:31:58.181
He doesn't care about
what anyone else has to say but himself.

01:31:58.264 --> 01:32:01.601
He just comes in and imposes his will
on all of us with no discussion.

01:32:01.684 --> 01:32:04.312
He doesn't listen.
I'm trying, but he doesn't listen.

01:32:04.395 --> 01:32:05.438
Mmm.

01:32:06.022 --> 01:32:08.399
-Sonny?
-What?

01:32:08.483 --> 01:32:09.943
[Joshua scoffs]

01:32:10.777 --> 01:32:13.530
[sighs] Wow. [scoffs]

01:32:13.613 --> 01:32:15.532
[sighs]

01:32:15.615 --> 01:32:18.326
♪ Why they lie to the people?
Why the world is so evil? ♪

01:32:18.409 --> 01:32:19.536
[no audible dialogue]

01:32:19.619 --> 01:32:23.373
♪ Why cant just cool?
Just let me cool ♪

01:32:23.957 --> 01:32:26.709
♪ Walking explosives
Stressing all of the time ♪

01:32:26.793 --> 01:32:28.086
Who taught you how to play?

01:32:28.169 --> 01:32:30.004
My dad liked to gamble.

01:32:30.588 --> 01:32:33.007
-He make big bets too?
-Put a big one on me.

01:32:33.091 --> 01:32:34.926
How old were you when your fathers died?

01:32:39.472 --> 01:32:40.473
Sorry.

01:32:40.557 --> 01:32:41.808
-Thirteen.
-Thirteen.

01:32:44.519 --> 01:32:46.020
Huh.

01:32:47.063 --> 01:32:48.273
Why do you race?

01:32:48.356 --> 01:32:52.318
Money… [sighs]
…fame and free clothes. [chuckles]

01:32:52.402 --> 01:32:54.612
Oh, my God, with the phone.
Put the thing down, will ya?

01:32:54.696 --> 01:32:56.489
What do you care what they say?

01:32:56.573 --> 01:32:58.366
Easy for you to say. They all love you.

01:32:58.449 --> 01:32:59.701
It's just noise, man.

01:33:01.244 --> 01:33:02.787
Drive the car.

01:33:02.871 --> 01:33:04.163
You're really good at it.

01:33:07.125 --> 01:33:08.418
You might be great.

01:33:25.602 --> 01:33:28.813
♪ Hyperbolic catastrophic scatterbrain ♪

01:33:28.897 --> 01:33:32.942
♪ This is one diabolic catatonic parade ♪

01:33:33.026 --> 01:33:35.486
♪ Everyone just go away
There's nothing new to celebrate ♪

01:33:35.570 --> 01:33:36.779
[Kate exhales heavily]

01:33:36.863 --> 01:33:38.907
♪ There's nowhere left to run away ♪

01:33:38.990 --> 01:33:42.911
♪ They're closing off the open seas
They're locking off the runways ♪

01:33:42.994 --> 01:33:47.290
♪ They keep telling me the one thing
So far from everything I see ♪

01:33:47.373 --> 01:33:48.708
♪ Just go away ♪

01:33:48.791 --> 01:33:51.085
[groans] Yeah. [chuckles]

01:33:51.169 --> 01:33:54.297
Look at that, huh?
Number one driver tomorrow.

01:33:54.380 --> 01:33:55.882
-Bonding?
-[Joshua] Ooh.

01:33:55.965 --> 01:33:56.966
Well, this is nice.

01:33:57.050 --> 01:33:59.052
We gotta go, mate. Sponsor party at OMNIA.

01:33:59.135 --> 01:34:00.303
Gotta steal ya.

01:34:00.887 --> 01:34:02.805
Uh, Uncle Sonny,
you're welcome to come with...

01:34:02.889 --> 01:34:04.609
Thank you, I'm good.
I have a race tomorrow.

01:34:05.183 --> 01:34:08.144
-Cool. Kate?
-No, thank you.

01:34:08.728 --> 01:34:10.439
-[manager] Come on.
-Thanks for this, Kate.

01:34:10.522 --> 01:34:13.608
[manager] Come on, boy.
Uh… Uh, girls, you might have to…

01:34:13.691 --> 01:34:15.652
We're gonna go dancing.
Should we go dancing?

01:34:15.735 --> 01:34:17.612
-Yeah!
-[all clamoring]

01:34:21.407 --> 01:34:23.368
[romantic pop song playing on speakers]

01:34:29.707 --> 01:34:30.959
Listen,

01:34:31.626 --> 01:34:33.211
let's get this straight, okay?

01:34:33.962 --> 01:34:37.382
I don't mess around during the season,
and never with a member of my team,

01:34:37.465 --> 01:34:39.175
and what I'm attracted to is winning.

01:34:39.926 --> 01:34:41.678
And you just lost to a pair of fives.

01:34:54.524 --> 01:34:59.821
♪ So, baby, let's get messy
Let's get all the way undone ♪

01:34:59.904 --> 01:35:04.784
♪ Come over, undress me
Just like I've never been touched ♪

01:35:04.868 --> 01:35:08.705
♪ Baby, I'm obsessed with you
And there's no replica ♪

01:35:08.788 --> 01:35:11.916
♪ Baby, let's get messy
Let's get all the way undone ♪

01:35:12.000 --> 01:35:13.501
[song continues as club remix]

01:35:27.015 --> 01:35:29.017
[energetic pop song plays]

01:35:30.810 --> 01:35:34.731
♪ I wanna let my hair down
While I'm staring down your face ♪

01:35:34.814 --> 01:35:38.234
♪ Wanna go till lights out
Take you right back to my place ♪

01:35:38.318 --> 01:35:41.613
♪ You out your mind
If you don't know what this is ♪

01:35:41.696 --> 01:35:42.697
Hey.

01:35:43.907 --> 01:35:45.366
You're a driver, aren't you?

01:35:46.284 --> 01:35:47.827
-Yeah.
-Which team?

01:35:47.911 --> 01:35:49.162
Apex GP.

01:35:49.245 --> 01:35:51.789
Can you introduce me to Carlos Sainz?

01:35:53.333 --> 01:35:54.459
I'll go get him.

01:35:54.542 --> 01:35:55.543
♪ Move from the back ♪

01:35:55.627 --> 01:35:57.545
♪ Eyes on me How you like that ♪

01:35:57.629 --> 01:35:59.339
♪ Just like this
Here for the night ♪

01:36:00.298 --> 01:36:02.133
Oh, hey. Hey.

01:36:02.217 --> 01:36:05.094
Oi, why do they say this place is weird?
I like this, bruv.

01:36:05.178 --> 01:36:07.472
Glad you're having fun, man.
Be safe. I'm gonna leave, yeah?

01:36:07.555 --> 01:36:08.806
-Huh?
-I said I'm gonna cut.

01:36:08.890 --> 01:36:11.560
-Oh, wait, no, no, no. You just got here!
-I just… I'm not feeling it.

01:36:11.643 --> 01:36:14.354
What do you mean?
We just got here, bruv. Josh!

01:36:16.147 --> 01:36:17.857
♪ Just keep watching ♪

01:36:18.900 --> 01:36:21.277
[car engine whirring]

01:36:37.460 --> 01:36:40.255
-[tires screech]
-[thuds]

01:36:42.340 --> 01:36:43.550
[screaming]

01:36:43.633 --> 01:36:46.803
[gasps, panting]

01:36:48.847 --> 01:36:49.848
[sighs]

01:37:11.953 --> 01:37:13.162
Hey.

01:37:15.290 --> 01:37:17.208
-[chuckles]
-[groans]

01:37:17.709 --> 01:37:19.210
I shouldn't drink tequila.

01:37:23.756 --> 01:37:25.175
Last night was Ruben's idea?

01:37:25.258 --> 01:37:26.926
[stammers] Yeah, the first part.

01:37:27.510 --> 01:37:30.597
-Well… [stammers, chuckles]
-Not the second! [chuckles]

01:37:41.024 --> 01:37:42.066
Come on.

01:37:43.234 --> 01:37:45.236
Why are you here, Sonny, huh?

01:37:48.489 --> 01:37:50.408
Not much of a story.

01:37:56.122 --> 01:37:57.207
Okay.

01:37:59.042 --> 01:38:00.960
I'm here to prove everyone wrong.

01:38:02.879 --> 01:38:05.548
My ex, my old boss,

01:38:07.258 --> 01:38:09.260
my first-year uni physics professor...

01:38:09.344 --> 01:38:10.887
-That bastard.
-Yeah.

01:38:10.970 --> 01:38:11.971
[chuckles]

01:38:13.181 --> 01:38:15.475
And until we win, I haven't.

01:38:16.684 --> 01:38:20.939
So, unfortunately, I now rely on you.

01:38:21.022 --> 01:38:22.065
Mmm.

01:38:27.820 --> 01:38:29.447
I was gonna be world champion.

01:38:31.074 --> 01:38:32.575
The best there ever was.

01:38:34.035 --> 01:38:36.454
I'm just a kid and I'm on the track
with my idols,

01:38:36.538 --> 01:38:38.748
Senna, Mansell, Prost.

01:38:38.831 --> 01:38:40.416
And I am quick.

01:38:41.835 --> 01:38:43.294
I'm fearless.

01:38:45.129 --> 01:38:46.422
I was next.

01:38:49.425 --> 01:38:50.426
And then…

01:38:51.928 --> 01:38:52.929
[clicks fingers]

01:38:53.847 --> 01:38:55.390
…it was all taken away.

01:38:57.725 --> 01:38:59.102
The crash, huh?

01:39:00.687 --> 01:39:04.482
So I lost my seat, my money,
my sanity, my…

01:39:05.441 --> 01:39:06.734
Myself, really.

01:39:07.694 --> 01:39:12.782
Just became this angry,
resentful shithead.

01:39:12.866 --> 01:39:16.536
[chuckles]
Not someone I'm particularly proud of.

01:39:20.915 --> 01:39:23.209
Till one day,
I realized what I had really lost,

01:39:23.293 --> 01:39:28.339
and it wasn't the titles,
or the trophies, or the records.

01:39:28.423 --> 01:39:31.759
It was my love for racing.

01:39:34.387 --> 01:39:36.097
So I started driving.

01:39:37.098 --> 01:39:40.643
Didn't matter the car, the circuit,
didn't need anyone to watch.

01:39:40.727 --> 01:39:44.606
Just as long as I was behind the wheel,
I was good.

01:39:47.775 --> 01:39:49.235
Sometimes…

01:39:55.700 --> 01:39:57.202
[sighs]

01:39:58.536 --> 01:40:01.414
What? Come on.

01:40:04.792 --> 01:40:10.256
It's rare, but sometimes,
there's this moment in the car

01:40:10.340 --> 01:40:12.967
where everything goes quiet,

01:40:13.843 --> 01:40:15.470
my heartbeat slows,

01:40:16.888 --> 01:40:18.348
it's peaceful,

01:40:19.015 --> 01:40:22.060
and I can see everything, and no one…

01:40:22.602 --> 01:40:24.229
No one can touch me.

01:40:27.273 --> 01:40:30.235
And I am chasing that moment
every time I get in the car.

01:40:33.321 --> 01:40:37.951
I don't know when I'll find it again,
but, man, I want to.

01:40:38.743 --> 01:40:40.203
[chuckles] I want to.

01:40:41.704 --> 01:40:44.916
'Cause in that moment, I'm flying.

01:40:56.427 --> 01:40:59.681
[doorbell rings]

01:41:07.021 --> 01:41:08.022
Kate.

01:41:08.565 --> 01:41:10.400
-Ruben.
-Where is he?

01:41:10.483 --> 01:41:11.609
Where's who?

01:41:12.443 --> 01:41:13.945
What are you talking about?

01:41:15.697 --> 01:41:17.115
Ruben, seriously?

01:41:18.074 --> 01:41:20.577
[scoffs] One, how dare you?

01:41:20.660 --> 01:41:23.329
Two, I respect professional boundaries.

01:41:24.122 --> 01:41:25.123
And three…

01:41:27.500 --> 01:41:29.086
Three, yeah, he's on… he's on the balcony.

01:41:29.169 --> 01:41:30.170
[grunts]

01:41:32.338 --> 01:41:34.049
-Well, you're up early.
-[Ruben] Get dressed.

01:41:34.132 --> 01:41:36.384
-Yeah, what's going on?
-They're coming for our car.

01:41:39.971 --> 01:41:43.016
[race director] It's my duty to inform you
that we've received an anonymous tip

01:41:43.099 --> 01:41:45.268
that your upgraded floor is in violation.

01:41:45.351 --> 01:41:46.561
[Ruben] From who?

01:41:46.644 --> 01:41:48.313
-I can't say.
-Ah. [chuckles]

01:41:48.396 --> 01:41:51.149
Sir, we submitted the drawings long ago.

01:41:51.232 --> 01:41:52.233
-Right?
-Mm-hmm.

01:41:52.317 --> 01:41:53.484
And you approved them all.

01:41:53.568 --> 01:41:58.114
It's whether the parts you're racing with
were developed outside of your facility.

01:41:58.198 --> 01:41:59.532
What? That's insane.

01:41:59.616 --> 01:42:02.285
Based on the paperwork we've received,
there are concerns.

01:42:02.368 --> 01:42:04.829
Hang on, where'd you get these?
These are internal documents.

01:42:04.913 --> 01:42:07.415
[Ruben] This team
doesn't break any rules, sir. No, no.

01:42:07.498 --> 01:42:10.460
-I'll take that with a pinch of salt.
-Someone can fabricate documents.

01:42:10.543 --> 01:42:11.836
Your car's under review.

01:42:11.920 --> 01:42:13.004
-You know the procedure.
-What?

01:42:13.087 --> 01:42:17.467
You cannot race unless you substitute
the previously approved components.

01:42:17.550 --> 01:42:19.677
-No!
-Do you mean our old design?

01:42:19.761 --> 01:42:20.887
A shit box!

01:42:20.970 --> 01:42:22.180
[in Spanish] No lo puedo creer.

01:42:22.263 --> 01:42:24.266
[in English] Where were you
the last two years? Why now?

01:42:24.349 --> 01:42:26.726
Because we might actually win a race?
Is that it?

01:42:26.809 --> 01:42:29.771
This is not car racing, sir,
this is like corporate espionage!

01:42:29.854 --> 01:42:31.898
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. Come… Come here.

01:42:31.981 --> 01:42:33.816
I'm talking to you! Sir!

01:42:33.900 --> 01:42:35.735
Without the upgrade, we're screwed.

01:43:02.345 --> 01:43:05.765
[Kaspar] Sonny, let it go.
Focus on a clean start.

01:43:05.849 --> 01:43:07.642
We'll never win clean.

01:43:08.226 --> 01:43:09.727
Can we just not break any rules?

01:43:09.811 --> 01:43:12.397
Yeah, the rules are always
against us though, aren't they?

01:43:15.900 --> 01:43:18.194
Get them safe through lap one. [sighs]

01:43:18.278 --> 01:43:21.197
[Hugh] Sonny, we just need
to keep it in one piece. Okay?

01:43:21.281 --> 01:43:24.033
[Sonny breathing shakily]

01:43:24.117 --> 01:43:26.578
[tense music playing]

01:43:26.661 --> 01:43:27.912
Sonny?

01:43:46.598 --> 01:43:47.891
[tires squeal]

01:43:52.395 --> 01:43:55.106
-Oi, what the hell?
-I don't know!

01:43:55.190 --> 01:43:56.233
[Joshua] What's wrong with Sonny?

01:43:56.316 --> 01:43:58.610
Joshua, yep. Keep focused.
You're still good.

01:43:58.693 --> 01:43:59.736
What's he doing?

01:44:06.242 --> 01:44:07.619
He's driving angry.

01:44:08.286 --> 01:44:09.621
Not good. It's not good.

01:44:16.794 --> 01:44:18.630
Sonny, we need to make these tires last.

01:44:18.713 --> 01:44:20.131
Take it easy.

01:44:27.013 --> 01:44:29.265
No, he's put the car in qualifying mode.

01:44:29.349 --> 01:44:31.560
He's gonna run the battery down.
Tell him to put it back.

01:44:31.643 --> 01:44:33.883
[Hugh] Sonny, you're in qualifying mode.
What's going on?

01:44:34.812 --> 01:44:35.813
Sonny, what's happening?

01:44:45.907 --> 01:44:50.328
[Croft] …blasting along
Las Vegas Boulevard, 210 miles an hour.

01:44:50.411 --> 01:44:52.872
Hard on the brakes now,
and into the chicane.

01:44:52.956 --> 01:44:57.460
Sergio Perez, ahead of Sonny Hayes,
but that's a mega exit from Hayes.

01:44:57.544 --> 01:45:00.672
He's gotta gain on Sergio Perez,
and he's closing.

01:45:00.755 --> 01:45:03.466
Meter by meter. Inch by inch.

01:45:03.550 --> 01:45:08.263
Is this the place to take a gamble?
Hayes attacks round the outside.

01:45:13.935 --> 01:45:15.937
[crowd gasping, clamoring]

01:45:16.437 --> 01:45:17.480
No! No!

01:45:27.657 --> 01:45:30.118
[somber orchestral music playing]

01:45:42.881 --> 01:45:45.341
Why do we do this?

01:45:45.967 --> 01:45:48.761
What's wrong with tennis, huh?

01:45:48.845 --> 01:45:50.430
-Or golf.
-[chuckles]

01:45:50.513 --> 01:45:52.182
[chuckles] Right?

01:45:53.141 --> 01:45:54.684
[exhales heavily]

01:45:55.518 --> 01:45:56.519
Christ.

01:45:58.479 --> 01:45:59.981
We are totally insane.

01:46:02.025 --> 01:46:03.026
[sighs]

01:46:04.986 --> 01:46:07.197
"C5 neck fracture."

01:46:08.531 --> 01:46:09.991
Spinal contusion.

01:46:10.533 --> 01:46:12.535
Compressed thoracic vertebrae.

01:46:13.119 --> 01:46:17.373
Further blunt force impact trauma
likely to result in vision loss,

01:46:17.457 --> 01:46:19.250
"paralysis, death."

01:46:22.504 --> 01:46:24.297
Really lead with the good news,
don't they?

01:46:24.964 --> 01:46:26.758
This is a report from 30 years ago.

01:46:28.468 --> 01:46:29.844
Why didn't you tell me?

01:46:32.680 --> 01:46:35.141
You never should have raced again, Sonny.

01:46:36.309 --> 01:46:38.853
How… How do you think I'd feel
if you die on the track?

01:46:40.980 --> 01:46:42.106
Revenge for Monaco.

01:46:42.190 --> 01:46:43.733
[stammers] It's not a joke!

01:46:46.945 --> 01:46:48.905
It's me who's liable, Sonny.

01:46:49.697 --> 01:46:52.575
And don't think there's some
bullshit loophole to get you out of this.

01:46:52.659 --> 01:46:54.118
-No.
-Ruben, we're drivers.

01:46:54.202 --> 01:46:56.913
We are not drivers, not anymore.
I'm sorry. We're not.

01:46:58.915 --> 01:47:00.208
We're losers.

01:47:01.918 --> 01:47:03.294
We're a pair of dumb,

01:47:03.920 --> 01:47:05.296
sentimental,

01:47:06.756 --> 01:47:07.966
broke losers.

01:47:11.845 --> 01:47:12.929
[sighs]

01:47:13.721 --> 01:47:15.139
Okay. You're off the team.

01:47:20.061 --> 01:47:23.815
[sighs] Your van is in the garage
with all your stuff in it, and…

01:47:28.361 --> 01:47:29.487
[chuckles]

01:47:30.363 --> 01:47:32.866
I never should have pulled you
into this, Sonny.

01:47:34.158 --> 01:47:35.368
I'm sorry.

01:47:37.954 --> 01:47:39.122
Ruben, wait!

01:47:40.623 --> 01:47:41.791
[sighs]

01:47:44.836 --> 01:47:45.962
I need this.

01:47:47.172 --> 01:47:48.173
[sighs]

01:47:48.923 --> 01:47:53.303
No one drives forever, Sonny.
Not even you.

01:48:07.859 --> 01:48:13.781
Pippa, load up Monza.
Just like it happened. In the rain.

01:48:14.991 --> 01:48:17.327
[crew member] Joshua,
Sonny says wait for the straight,

01:48:17.410 --> 01:48:19.370
the straight into turn one.

01:48:27.212 --> 01:48:28.463
Run it again, please.

01:48:32.967 --> 01:48:35.929
[crew member] …wait for the straight,
the straight into turn one.

01:48:38.556 --> 01:48:40.391
Run it again, please.

01:48:50.109 --> 01:48:52.111
[crew member] The straight into turn one.

01:48:58.576 --> 01:49:02.539
[exclaims] Whoo! [chuckles]

01:49:19.556 --> 01:49:20.849
[Peter] Sonny.

01:49:22.100 --> 01:49:23.142
Sonny.

01:49:24.394 --> 01:49:26.312
Hey. You're not in Abu Dhabi?

01:49:26.396 --> 01:49:28.857
I fly out tonight. I, uh…

01:49:28.940 --> 01:49:30.233
Yeah, I wanted to catch you.

01:49:31.776 --> 01:49:33.069
So, listen. [sighs]

01:49:33.152 --> 01:49:37.031
We both know that the board's
wanted to unload Apex from the start,

01:49:37.699 --> 01:49:40.702
but, yeah, then you rode into town,

01:49:40.785 --> 01:49:43.371
raised our whole profile,
and now I've, uh…

01:49:43.454 --> 01:49:45.915
Yeah, I've got… I've got buyers lining up.

01:49:47.834 --> 01:49:49.669
-Uh-huh.
-Gotta be honest with you, man,

01:49:49.752 --> 01:49:52.672
I thought you were gonna be the…
the final nail in the coffin.

01:49:53.256 --> 01:49:54.841
But now I see the play.

01:49:54.924 --> 01:49:58.553
And I want you as part of the package.

01:50:01.890 --> 01:50:03.433
What sort of package?

01:50:04.100 --> 01:50:06.853
I've set up a sale where I run the team,

01:50:06.936 --> 01:50:08.521
and keep you on for strategy,

01:50:09.314 --> 01:50:10.648
maybe even team principal.

01:50:11.983 --> 01:50:15.820
With the money from that deal,
I can make you a very rich man.

01:50:16.863 --> 01:50:18.239
Here's the thing.

01:50:18.323 --> 01:50:20.450
With the… the changing regulations,

01:50:20.533 --> 01:50:23.870
new Mercedes power unit,
Kate's aero, two new drivers…

01:50:25.246 --> 01:50:27.332
We've got a real shot
at the championship next year.

01:50:28.625 --> 01:50:29.834
What about Ruben?

01:50:29.918 --> 01:50:30.919
Don't worry.

01:50:31.669 --> 01:50:32.962
You know.

01:50:33.046 --> 01:50:34.172
We won't embarrass him.

01:50:34.839 --> 01:50:37.717
We'll keep him on with a… with a title,
or brand ambassador…

01:50:38.343 --> 01:50:39.427
You know, something.

01:50:43.515 --> 01:50:44.766
And I get final say?

01:50:44.849 --> 01:50:46.059
Don't change a thing.

01:50:46.142 --> 01:50:47.310
Do what you do, man.

01:50:48.353 --> 01:50:49.812
And that's the irony here.

01:50:49.896 --> 01:50:52.732
You know, the board
originally approved your hire

01:50:52.815 --> 01:50:54.359
because we thought you'd help us lose.

01:50:55.235 --> 01:50:56.569
-Sorry to make you sweat.
-Hey.

01:50:58.279 --> 01:50:59.405
That's my number.

01:50:59.489 --> 01:51:00.740
Talk to your people.

01:51:01.282 --> 01:51:07.205
But, uh… [chuckles] …right after the race,
I, uh… I wanna lock down the deal, okay?

01:51:07.705 --> 01:51:09.666
-So, by Sunday?
-Perfect.

01:51:10.834 --> 01:51:13.711
Listen, this thing can be your legacy,
you know?

01:51:15.839 --> 01:51:17.048
An F1 champion.

01:51:18.299 --> 01:51:19.717
What you always wanted, right?

01:51:23.263 --> 01:51:26.766
It was you who forged those documents,
wasn't it?

01:51:26.850 --> 01:51:27.851
Huh.

01:51:30.520 --> 01:51:32.355
[chuckles]

01:51:33.189 --> 01:51:36.025
-You're a killer, man, aren't you?
-Hey. I'm a winner.

01:51:37.652 --> 01:51:40.154
-Aren't you, huh?
-[sighs]

01:51:42.282 --> 01:51:43.283
Okay.

01:51:46.286 --> 01:51:48.621
Oh, hey. How's the back?

01:51:49.622 --> 01:51:50.748
Better.

01:51:50.832 --> 01:51:53.418
I've got an amazing guy.
I'll, uh… I'll hook you up.

01:51:54.711 --> 01:51:55.712
Hail Mary.

01:52:23.323 --> 01:52:24.449
You good?

01:52:29.162 --> 01:52:33.041
[sighs] Listen, Mum,
I've gotta tell you something.

01:52:36.920 --> 01:52:41.966
In Monza, right before the crash,
it was my decision to make the move.

01:52:43.384 --> 01:52:45.136
Sonny actually told me to wait.

01:52:47.138 --> 01:52:50.266
[breathes deeply]

01:52:52.852 --> 01:52:53.937
[knocks on door]

01:52:54.020 --> 01:52:55.146
Family.

01:52:55.230 --> 01:52:57.649
I've been working the phones with IndyCar,

01:52:57.732 --> 01:52:59.526
and I think I can get you
a test drive, bruv.

01:52:59.609 --> 01:53:00.818
-Hello, Auntie. [kisses]
-Hi.

01:53:02.070 --> 01:53:04.531
They're trying to pull in
a new demographic, obviously.

01:53:04.614 --> 01:53:07.325
And the ladies love that smile.

01:53:07.909 --> 01:53:10.620
And we can throw in some incentives,
like flights and cars.

01:53:10.703 --> 01:53:12.747
Listen, Cash, you can go.
I don't need you today.

01:53:13.831 --> 01:53:15.333
Nah, mate. You got media next.

01:53:15.416 --> 01:53:18.002
[chuckles] I don't care. They can fine me.

01:53:18.795 --> 01:53:19.796
Besides,

01:53:21.297 --> 01:53:22.924
that's not why I'm doing it, right?

01:53:23.842 --> 01:53:26.002
Josh, starting tomorrow,
we're not "doing it" anywhere.

01:53:27.637 --> 01:53:29.097
It's all just noise.

01:53:30.014 --> 01:53:32.183
Media, engagement, followers.

01:53:32.892 --> 01:53:36.062
Listen, I've gotta focus on the race.

01:53:37.897 --> 01:53:39.566
[Cash] Auntie, please.

01:53:41.192 --> 01:53:42.527
Well, you heard the man.

01:53:51.578 --> 01:53:54.122
-Deal.
-Deal. [chuckles]

01:53:57.083 --> 01:53:59.127
-Yo.
-Hey.

01:53:59.210 --> 01:54:00.712
-Hi.
-Hey.

01:54:03.673 --> 01:54:05.717
Guys, what's happening?

01:54:05.800 --> 01:54:08.970
Parc fermé.
Waiting for FIA to cut the seals.

01:54:09.053 --> 01:54:11.097
Oh, good. [sighs]

01:54:11.681 --> 01:54:14.142
-We got time then.
-For what?

01:54:15.101 --> 01:54:16.311
For…

01:54:17.812 --> 01:54:19.397
[chuckles]

01:54:19.480 --> 01:54:21.649
No, no, no.

01:54:26.237 --> 01:54:29.532
Welcome to the Paddock Club,
for our most valued guests.

01:54:29.616 --> 01:54:33.536
Please, uh, grab a drink,
make yourselves at home,

01:54:33.620 --> 01:54:37.916
and, uh, enjoy the very best view
there is of, uh… of Formula 1.

01:54:39.959 --> 01:54:41.461
Okay? Okay.

01:54:45.173 --> 01:54:46.341
[clears throat]

01:54:59.229 --> 01:55:01.397
Hey, guys, don't stop! Keep going!

01:55:04.317 --> 01:55:07.487
[chuckles]

01:55:11.449 --> 01:55:14.285
[sighing]

01:55:15.703 --> 01:55:16.788
[groans]

01:55:31.719 --> 01:55:34.097
[stirring orchestral music playing]

01:55:37.100 --> 01:55:40.019
No way. [chuckles]

01:55:43.857 --> 01:55:45.024
[sighs]

01:55:47.485 --> 01:55:50.405
Jesús, it's like a morgue around here.

01:55:52.740 --> 01:55:54.242
[stammers] How'd you get here?

01:55:54.325 --> 01:55:55.702
Premium economy.

01:55:56.536 --> 01:55:58.121
[Ruben scoffs]

01:55:59.956 --> 01:56:01.833
What? What is this?

01:56:01.916 --> 01:56:03.501
Well, that's my bullshit loophole.

01:56:03.585 --> 01:56:05.712
Oh, no, forget it.
I'm not even going to read that.

01:56:05.795 --> 01:56:08.339
That is a real legal document
from a real Tijuana lawyer…

01:56:08.423 --> 01:56:10.175
-[chuckles]
-…waiving all liability to you

01:56:10.258 --> 01:56:12.802
and your company vis-à-vis this race,
myself, and me.

01:56:13.887 --> 01:56:15.138
-And…
-[inhales sharply]

01:56:17.724 --> 01:56:21.144
…since you owe me my last paycheck,
technically I'm still on this team.

01:56:26.399 --> 01:56:27.901
Kate, where's the shitbox?

01:56:28.568 --> 01:56:30.987
The FIA confirmed that
the documents were forged,

01:56:31.070 --> 01:56:33.114
and they were sent by someone from Apex.

01:56:33.948 --> 01:56:35.033
Huh.

01:56:35.658 --> 01:56:38.620
Okay, I don't care about your loophole.
I don't.

01:56:38.703 --> 01:56:40.747
That is my car. You are not racing it.

01:56:40.830 --> 01:56:41.956
-Ruben.
-No, Sonny.

01:56:42.040 --> 01:56:43.333
Listen,

01:56:44.584 --> 01:56:46.377
I can't let you do that.

01:56:46.461 --> 01:56:47.462
I can't.

01:56:47.545 --> 01:56:48.671
Okay?

01:56:48.755 --> 01:56:49.756
[stammers]

01:56:50.423 --> 01:56:54.052
If the last thing I do is drive that car,
I will take that life, man.

01:56:57.931 --> 01:56:59.349
A thousand times.

01:57:01.309 --> 01:57:03.019
[sighs]

01:57:04.103 --> 01:57:05.355
We can't win.

01:57:07.190 --> 01:57:08.608
We can't if we don't try.

01:57:15.031 --> 01:57:16.032
[sighs]

01:57:19.619 --> 01:57:20.828
[sighs]

01:57:28.336 --> 01:57:30.129
[laughing]

01:57:31.798 --> 01:57:33.508
[laughs]

01:57:44.435 --> 01:57:46.729
[groaning]

01:57:47.939 --> 01:57:48.940
[knocks on door]

01:57:54.904 --> 01:57:56.406
How come you never look at the card?

01:57:56.489 --> 01:57:57.657
[Sonny] What card?

01:57:57.740 --> 01:57:58.741
[chuckles]

01:57:59.951 --> 01:58:02.412
[crowd cheering]

01:58:38.865 --> 01:58:41.284
Welcome to the very final spots
on the grid.

01:58:41.367 --> 01:58:45.747
And as ever, we'll go from last to first.
And breaking news here in P22,

01:58:45.830 --> 01:58:47.415
because we're hearing
the Apex GP team have made…

01:58:47.498 --> 01:58:49.209
-Hey, Peter.
-Yeah?

01:58:49.792 --> 01:58:51.044
That's your guy. Isn't it?

01:58:51.127 --> 01:58:55.131
…being replaced by Sonny Hayes, who
didn't even make the trip to Abu Dhabi…

01:58:55.215 --> 01:58:57.759
Uh, will you excuse me for one second?
I'm really sorry.

01:58:57.842 --> 01:59:00.637
Now, the rules require that
he has to start at the back of the pack.

01:59:01.304 --> 01:59:03.598
Excuse me. What the hell?

01:59:04.349 --> 01:59:05.558
What?

01:59:09.729 --> 01:59:10.813
You still got my phone?

01:59:14.651 --> 01:59:15.652
[phone buzzes]

01:59:29.791 --> 01:59:31.334
-Good luck today.
-You too, James.

01:59:31.417 --> 01:59:32.544
Excuse me. Hey, Sonny. Sonny!

01:59:32.627 --> 01:59:34.171
Hey, look,
I know we've had our differences,

01:59:34.254 --> 01:59:36.464
-but look, this is your last F1 race.
-Chaz! This guy.

01:59:36.548 --> 01:59:37.841
Any thought…

01:59:40.009 --> 01:59:41.010
What's that?

01:59:42.303 --> 01:59:44.097
[crowd cheering]

01:59:45.139 --> 01:59:46.432
Bloody hell.

01:59:48.351 --> 01:59:49.602
Bloody hell!

01:59:50.103 --> 01:59:51.646
[laughs]

01:59:51.729 --> 01:59:54.148
[UAE national anthem playing]

02:00:10.290 --> 02:00:11.291
Elbows out?

02:00:11.958 --> 02:00:12.959
Elbows out.

02:00:14.752 --> 02:00:20.300
[Croft] All set for our season finale
here in Abu Dhabi where it's lights out.

02:00:20.383 --> 02:00:23.928
And away we go.
Good start there for Joshua Pearce.

02:00:24.012 --> 02:00:26.181
Drivers jockeying for position

02:00:26.264 --> 02:00:30.894
as we head full-throttle
down the main straight and into turn one.

02:00:30.977 --> 02:00:35.815
Tricky first corner, and going wide,
the Aston Martin and the AlphaTauri

02:00:35.899 --> 02:00:38.067
-[laughs]
-as Pearce picks up two places.

02:00:38.151 --> 02:00:40.528
[Brundle] Yes, Pearce showing
some real maturity there.

02:00:40.612 --> 02:00:44.699
He saw a bad situation before it happened
and he's off to a great start.

02:01:03.259 --> 02:01:04.636
Don't even think about it.

02:01:20.610 --> 02:01:23.530
[Croft] Here comes the Alpine
down the inside. Contact!

02:01:24.781 --> 02:01:27.909
And three days out of hospital,
Hayes will feel that.

02:01:37.752 --> 02:01:39.796
Gained places, guys. We're alive.

02:01:39.879 --> 02:01:41.465
[Brundle]
I hope he hasn't damaged the car,

02:01:41.548 --> 02:01:44.425
but despite everything,
it's still a great first lap.

02:01:44.509 --> 02:01:46.511
[Croft] It is! Hayes in P16.

02:01:46.594 --> 02:01:49.138
Pearce, his teammate, up to P9.

02:01:51.099 --> 02:01:54.435
Red Bull, Mercedes and Ferrari
holding on to the lead.

02:01:54.519 --> 02:01:56.229
Apex in the midfield.

02:01:56.312 --> 02:01:59.232
Let's see if they can do anything
to shake up this race.

02:01:59.315 --> 02:02:00.400
Gap to leader?

02:02:00.483 --> 02:02:01.526
[Hugh] Fifteen seconds.

02:02:02.735 --> 02:02:05.280
Keep JP plus 20 seconds. Plus 20.

02:02:05.864 --> 02:02:07.699
-Length of a pit stop.
-You know why.

02:02:09.200 --> 02:02:11.077
[Croft] It's a busy race for Sonny Hayes,

02:02:11.160 --> 02:02:14.247
and now here comes Kevin Magnussen
looking to make a move.

02:02:14.330 --> 02:02:16.040
And this could spell trouble.

02:02:16.124 --> 02:02:17.751
[Brundle]
There's history between these two.

02:02:17.834 --> 02:02:21.171
Often, the irresistible force
meets the immovable object.

02:02:21.254 --> 02:02:23.173
And Magnussen, looking down the inside,

02:02:23.256 --> 02:02:26.801
-locks up and hits Hayes.
-Box, box. Box, box, box.

02:02:26.885 --> 02:02:28.261
Copy, coming in for hards.

02:02:29.846 --> 02:02:31.097
Damn.

02:02:32.599 --> 02:02:35.810
Slow is smooth. Smooth is fast.
Here we go, boys.

02:02:43.109 --> 02:02:44.319
[Croft] Hayes exit the pits.

02:02:44.402 --> 02:02:47.197
He had to come in
because of that damage to his tire.

02:02:47.280 --> 02:02:51.326
But what of Joshua Pearce?
Where do Apex GP go with him?

02:02:53.036 --> 02:02:54.954
[Joshua] Guys, am I boxing?
What's the plan?

02:02:55.038 --> 02:02:57.457
Plan C, Plan C. Stay out. Stay out.

02:02:57.540 --> 02:03:00.210
-[laughs] Chaos.
-Copy that.

02:03:00.293 --> 02:03:03.796
Joshua slows down the leaders for Sonny.
Sonny does the same for him.

02:03:05.215 --> 02:03:06.758
[Brundle] Pearce stays out.

02:03:06.841 --> 02:03:09.844
It's a strategy that Apex have used
before this season.

02:03:09.928 --> 02:03:13.932
It helps them with track position for now,
but they gotta keep these tires alive.

02:03:17.477 --> 02:03:19.145
It's the only way we keep this close.

02:03:19.729 --> 02:03:20.772
And then we need luck.

02:03:20.855 --> 02:03:22.148
I'm way ahead of ya.

02:03:23.733 --> 02:03:24.733
[Rico chuckles]

02:03:25.443 --> 02:03:29.030
[Croft] Lap 25, and every driver
so far has pitted, bar one.

02:03:29.113 --> 02:03:30.865
And he leads the race.

02:03:30.949 --> 02:03:33.868
Joshua Pearce controlling the pace
out in front.

02:03:33.952 --> 02:03:35.662
[Brundle] And that gives
his teammate, Hayes,

02:03:35.745 --> 02:03:38.122
a chance to maintain
his position in the midfield

02:03:38.206 --> 02:03:41.417
despite the contact,
puncture and pit stop.

02:03:41.501 --> 02:03:43.127
They're working really well together.

02:03:44.921 --> 02:03:46.089
How's JP doing up there?

02:03:46.172 --> 02:03:49.384
He's keeping the leaders at bay.
DRS active next straight, Sonny.

02:03:49.467 --> 02:03:50.760
Got it.

02:03:51.594 --> 02:03:55.139
[Croft] Onto the back straight.
He's enjoying this new upgrade,

02:03:55.223 --> 02:03:58.393
and he's got DRS,
and he's got Pierre Gasly.

02:03:58.476 --> 02:04:00.562
Sonny Hayes up into P15.

02:04:01.688 --> 02:04:04.065
[Hugh] Sonny, you have got the pace.
Keep pushing.

02:04:04.649 --> 02:04:06.610
[Brundle] Pearce has been doing
a great job out front

02:04:06.693 --> 02:04:10.280
despite the used tires,
but that moment is nearly over now.

02:04:10.363 --> 02:04:13.199
Verstappen up the inside and he's through.

02:04:13.283 --> 02:04:15.785
[Croft] Fabulous first stint
from Joshua Pearce.

02:04:15.869 --> 02:04:18.246
Max has passed,
and his troubles don't end there.

02:04:19.581 --> 02:04:21.457
Here comes Charles Leclerc.

02:04:21.541 --> 02:04:25.795
It's another overtake.
Pearce lost the lead and drops now to P3.

02:04:25.879 --> 02:04:28.339
Sorry, guys. My rear tires are shot.

02:04:28.423 --> 02:04:30.216
Copy that. Box, JP. Box, box.

02:04:31.801 --> 02:04:33.970
[Brundle] Pearce stretching those tires
to the limit.

02:04:34.053 --> 02:04:36.973
Short-term pain for long-term gain.

02:04:45.190 --> 02:04:48.151
And he exits the pit.
He'll have fresher tires.

02:04:48.234 --> 02:04:51.362
He can now attack
in the second half of the race.

02:04:51.946 --> 02:04:53.781
Sonny, the three leaders
are still on hards.

02:04:53.865 --> 02:04:55.784
They're gonna have to stop again.
This is their pit window.

02:04:55.867 --> 02:04:58.870
One of the leaders is gonna undercut.
I need to be there when they do.

02:05:00.288 --> 02:05:02.582
P3 Ferrari. Pippa, can he beat it to one?

02:05:05.126 --> 02:05:06.211
[Pippa] Depends on their stop.

02:05:06.294 --> 02:05:08.046
[Croft] Will the undercut
work for Ferrari?

02:05:08.129 --> 02:05:10.423
Five point eight.
He needs to pick up half a second.

02:05:12.634 --> 02:05:15.011
Sonny, you need half a second.
Go, go, go, go, go.

02:05:15.094 --> 02:05:16.513
[Croft] And Sonny Hayes is on the charge.

02:05:16.596 --> 02:05:19.015
Under the track goes the Ferrari.

02:05:19.098 --> 02:05:21.017
Through the first corner goes Sonny Hayes.

02:05:21.100 --> 02:05:23.770
It's neck and neck. It's really tight.

02:05:23.853 --> 02:05:27.357
Sonny Hayes is just ahead of Carlos Sainz.

02:05:27.440 --> 02:05:29.692
-Yes! Come on!
-[Croft] It's worked so far for Apex GP.

02:05:29.776 --> 02:05:31.569
But their trouble's not over.

02:05:31.653 --> 02:05:35.865
Down the inside, there's a chance
for Carlos Sainz, and he takes it.

02:05:35.949 --> 02:05:37.158
But he locks up.

02:05:37.242 --> 02:05:39.953
The Ferrari goes wide
and Sonny Hayes says,

02:05:40.036 --> 02:05:42.705
"Thank you very much indeed."

02:05:44.332 --> 02:05:46.417
How are they staying so close to the lead?

02:05:46.501 --> 02:05:49.671
Uh, they're, um… They're working together.

02:05:50.338 --> 02:05:53.842
[Brundle] Two Apex cars in the top 10,
but still a long way to go.

02:05:55.510 --> 02:05:59.347
[Croft] Twenty laps remaining, and Apex
has worked their way up the order.

02:05:59.430 --> 02:06:01.724
We're now at the final pit stop window.

02:06:01.808 --> 02:06:04.394
This is our chance for P1.
Make sure JP beats them out.

02:06:04.477 --> 02:06:09.148
[Croft] Hamilton and Leclerc
come into the pits, but Pearce stays out.

02:06:10.191 --> 02:06:12.944
-[Joshua] Talk to me. Can I catch 'em?
-Yep. They're just coming out.

02:06:13.027 --> 02:06:14.821
Push now. Push now. Push, push.

02:06:14.904 --> 02:06:16.197
Copy. Pushing.

02:06:16.781 --> 02:06:18.366
[Croft] Oh, this is gonna be close.

02:06:18.449 --> 02:06:21.411
Joshua Pearce inching ahead.
Staying ahead.

02:06:21.494 --> 02:06:24.289
For the second time in this race,
he leads.

02:06:24.372 --> 02:06:25.373
[laughs] Let's go!

02:06:25.456 --> 02:06:26.958
-[grunts]
-[grunts] Yes.

02:06:27.041 --> 02:06:30.044
You are P1, Joshua. [laughs]

02:06:30.128 --> 02:06:32.505
[Brundle] But Pearce will have
a hard time holding them off

02:06:32.589 --> 02:06:35.508
with Hamilton and Leclerc on fresh tires.

02:06:44.726 --> 02:06:47.103
[Croft] Four laps to go.
Sonny Hayes is in P4.

02:06:47.187 --> 02:06:49.105
He's five seconds behind his teammate,

02:06:49.189 --> 02:06:50.899
but both are on old tires.

02:06:50.982 --> 02:06:53.610
There's little chance
they'll gain any places now.

02:06:55.862 --> 02:06:59.824
And here's Hamilton
attacking Pearce into turn five.

02:06:59.908 --> 02:07:01.159
And he's through.

02:07:01.242 --> 02:07:05.079
Nobody has to stop again
and our tires are nine laps older.

02:07:06.831 --> 02:07:09.375
[Brundle] And Leclerc attacks and passes.

02:07:09.459 --> 02:07:13.880
Pearce's tires are absolutely finished.
There was nothing he could do about that.

02:07:14.631 --> 02:07:17.717
I'm sorry, guys. I've got nothing left.

02:07:17.800 --> 02:07:21.262
[Croft] It's been the Apex GP story
all year long.

02:07:21.346 --> 02:07:22.347
Plenty of risks.

02:07:22.430 --> 02:07:24.057
A great underdog story,

02:07:24.140 --> 02:07:26.142
but we know, Martin,
only talent crowns a champion.

02:07:26.226 --> 02:07:27.727
[Sonny] Losing grip. Tires are gone.

02:07:27.810 --> 02:07:30.438
[Brundle] Yeah. Sadly, the deck's
been stacked against them

02:07:30.522 --> 02:07:32.398
and now they're out of cards to play.

02:07:32.482 --> 02:07:33.566
It ain't over, right?

02:07:33.650 --> 02:07:36.945
No, but nothing can change.
It's the worst feeling in the world.

02:07:41.574 --> 02:07:43.368
George Russell on the attack.

02:07:43.451 --> 02:07:46.287
Hayes looking to defend,
through the left-hander they go…

02:07:46.371 --> 02:07:47.789
And there's contact!

02:07:47.872 --> 02:07:50.625
Hayes is spun round and into the barrier.

02:07:50.708 --> 02:07:52.418
That's a big one.

02:07:52.502 --> 02:07:53.503
[gasping]

02:07:54.128 --> 02:07:56.464
-Fucking yes, yes, yes.
-Oh, no.

02:07:57.674 --> 02:07:58.675
Yeah, no. Ooh.

02:07:58.758 --> 02:08:00.427
[Brundle] There's debris
all over the race track

02:08:00.510 --> 02:08:02.929
and substantial damage to the barriers.

02:08:03.012 --> 02:08:06.182
The stewards have no choice
but to red flag this race.

02:08:06.266 --> 02:08:07.267
Miracle.

02:08:07.350 --> 02:08:09.102
[Croft] And speaking of damage, Martin,

02:08:09.185 --> 02:08:11.729
Hayes will only be allowed
to continue in this race

02:08:11.813 --> 02:08:15.024
if he can get his car
all the way around the circuit

02:08:15.108 --> 02:08:16.484
and back to the pit lane.

02:08:17.068 --> 02:08:19.320
[Hugh] Sonny. Sonny, can you get it back?

02:08:19.404 --> 02:08:22.115
I'll get it back. I'll get it back
if I have to push it back.

02:08:22.699 --> 02:08:27.120
Come on, Sonny. Nice and easy.

02:08:27.203 --> 02:08:29.706
[grunting]

02:08:29.789 --> 02:08:32.500
He's still going.
[chuckling] He's still going.

02:08:32.584 --> 02:08:34.002
[crew member] JP, red flag.

02:08:34.085 --> 02:08:35.295
Red flag. Come in.

02:08:35.378 --> 02:08:39.716
We are still alive, hermano. [laughs]

02:08:39.799 --> 02:08:41.426
Red flag!

02:08:41.509 --> 02:08:45.138
[Brundle] And somehow Sonny Hayes
has got his car back to the pit lane.

02:08:45.221 --> 02:08:47.390
-It's a miracle.
-I know! I know.

02:08:47.473 --> 02:08:48.766
Never seen one until now.

02:08:48.850 --> 02:08:52.270
Home free. Good girl. Let's go.

02:08:52.979 --> 02:08:53.980
New softs, both cars.

02:08:54.063 --> 02:08:56.524
Raise the tire pressure
for three quick laps.

02:08:56.608 --> 02:08:58.693
-Team, time to build a car.
-[crew cheers, clamors]

02:08:58.776 --> 02:09:00.153
[Croft] Red flag rules then.

02:09:00.236 --> 02:09:03.531
The teams can make changes.
They can make repairs to their cars.

02:09:03.615 --> 02:09:04.991
But only in that pit lane.

02:09:05.074 --> 02:09:09.996
And with only ten minutes to make repairs,
Apex GP has their work cut out.

02:09:10.496 --> 02:09:13.875
[Brundle] And all cars
can fit a fresh set of tires

02:09:13.958 --> 02:09:15.919
for what will be a three-lap sprint.

02:09:16.002 --> 02:09:18.922
-Dodge! Dodge, are we gonna make it?
-I don't know. I don't know.

02:09:24.761 --> 02:09:27.347
That was clean.
That wasn't me. Not this time.

02:09:27.430 --> 02:09:31.142
"Not this time"?
Tell that to the stewards.

02:09:31.226 --> 02:09:32.477
Check the replay.

02:09:33.520 --> 02:09:35.438
I got this. Lift that corner.

02:09:43.821 --> 02:09:46.574
I'm good. I'm good, I'm good. I'm good.

02:09:46.658 --> 02:09:48.201
[Brundle] What the stewards
will be looking at

02:09:48.284 --> 02:09:50.119
is whether Hayes went off completely

02:09:50.203 --> 02:09:54.165
or kept at least one tire on track
during the contact with Russell.

02:09:54.249 --> 02:09:55.959
-Yo, you good?
-Yeah, good.

02:09:56.042 --> 02:09:57.252
Listen, you were on track.

02:09:57.335 --> 02:10:00.380
Yeah, it was your corner.
P3 and P4. Let's go!

02:10:00.463 --> 02:10:04.425
[Croft] Given Hayes's reputation, they'll
be looking at this really, really closely.

02:10:04.509 --> 02:10:06.177
I'm not expecting a quick decision.

02:10:06.261 --> 02:10:07.762
Come on, that's clearly a penalty.

02:10:07.846 --> 02:10:09.764
Like… I mean,
not that that's what we want,

02:10:09.848 --> 02:10:13.476
but, like, objectively, that's the guy.

02:10:13.560 --> 02:10:16.229
-Oh, man. It can't end this way.
-It's just a time-out.

02:10:16.312 --> 02:10:20.316
Like the last 30 years.
It's in the hands of the racing gods now.

02:10:20.400 --> 02:10:22.235
We gotta believe. Gotta believe.

02:10:23.736 --> 02:10:25.822
[Croft] Plenty going on here in the pit.

02:10:25.905 --> 02:10:29.075
Oh, look. Here comes the new wing.
This is a massive job.

02:10:29.158 --> 02:10:33.121
Yeah, but will the car hold together
for the remaining three laps?

02:10:36.332 --> 02:10:38.293
Well, that barrier looks okay now.

02:10:38.376 --> 02:10:41.754
The marshals just sweeping
the last few bits of debris off the track,

02:10:41.838 --> 02:10:43.923
and the clock continues to tick down.

02:10:44.007 --> 02:10:47.927
[Brundle] Yeah, it's just over two minutes
until this race gets underway again.

02:11:08.907 --> 02:11:10.366
JP, JP!

02:11:11.659 --> 02:11:12.785
Three laps.

02:11:12.869 --> 02:11:14.287
Three laps is a lifetime.

02:11:14.370 --> 02:11:15.705
Go win this thing.

02:11:27.634 --> 02:11:30.220
Hey, Sonny. Sonny, you got a minute?

02:11:32.430 --> 02:11:33.473
We got you a car.

02:11:34.140 --> 02:11:36.893
Ah, you rock. Thank you.

02:11:39.479 --> 02:11:42.774
[Brundle] Because Apex GP
didn't make the top 10 in qualifying,

02:11:42.857 --> 02:11:45.652
they have a new set
of soft tires available,

02:11:45.735 --> 02:11:49.030
which will give them extra speed
over the cars ahead of them

02:11:49.113 --> 02:11:51.366
on the used soft tires.

02:11:51.449 --> 02:11:54.327
This red flag is a lifeline.

02:11:54.410 --> 02:11:56.746
You'd almost wonder
if Sonny didn't engineer it.

02:11:57.580 --> 02:12:00.375
But wait, we're the only cars
on fresh tires

02:12:00.458 --> 02:12:02.210
because we sucked in qualifying yesterday?

02:12:02.293 --> 02:12:03.962
Never got the chance to use them.

02:12:04.045 --> 02:12:06.297
Sometimes when you lose, you win.

02:12:06.381 --> 02:12:08.883
-That don't make no sense.
-It's a Sonny thing.

02:12:09.759 --> 02:12:11.761
[Croft] Light at the end of the pit lane
is green.

02:12:11.845 --> 02:12:15.014
We're off on our second formation lap
of the evening,

02:12:15.098 --> 02:12:18.685
and when this race resumes,
this is gonna be an epic sprint.

02:12:18.768 --> 02:12:21.771
Hamilton, Leclerc, Pearce, Hayes.
That's the top four.

02:12:46.004 --> 02:12:47.964
[Hugh] Sonny, we just heard
from the stewards.

02:12:48.047 --> 02:12:49.048
Goddamn it. Now?

02:12:49.132 --> 02:12:50.759
[Hugh] We're debating whether to tell you.

02:12:50.842 --> 02:12:53.011
Kaspar says, "Yes,"
but Kate says, "Don't."

02:12:53.094 --> 02:12:55.221
-She says you're fast when you're angry.
-[chuckles]

02:12:55.305 --> 02:12:57.307
-Tell her, "Job well done."
-[laughs]

02:12:57.390 --> 02:13:00.435
[Croft] And here's news.
Stewards have made their decision.

02:13:00.518 --> 02:13:05.857
That Lap 55 collision between Hayes
and Russell is ruled a racing incident.

02:13:05.940 --> 02:13:08.109
-No further investigation.
-[cheering]

02:13:08.193 --> 02:13:10.236
Whoa! Sonny.

02:13:13.114 --> 02:13:16.492
That was your line, Sonny.
Go finish your race.

02:13:19.662 --> 02:13:22.373
Joshua, we still got two cars in the mix.

02:13:22.457 --> 02:13:23.833
Then we've got a team.

02:13:25.001 --> 02:13:26.503
[Brundle] Once those red lights go out,

02:13:26.586 --> 02:13:29.506
this will be an absolute sprint
to the finish.

02:13:30.381 --> 02:13:32.884
Position advantage to Mercedes
and Ferrari.

02:13:32.967 --> 02:13:35.345
Tire advantage to Apex GP.

02:14:01.871 --> 02:14:03.498
Tell JP to follow my lead.

02:14:03.581 --> 02:14:05.375
[crew member]
Joshua, Sonny says to follow him.

02:14:05.458 --> 02:14:07.043
Follow? He's behind me.

02:14:09.295 --> 02:14:11.923
-Cheeky bastard.
-[Sonny] That's it. Stay with me.

02:14:20.974 --> 02:14:22.476
[crew member] He's giving you a tow.
Take it.

02:14:22.559 --> 02:14:23.685
All the way.

02:14:51.171 --> 02:14:53.214
Come on, kid. Get it. Come on!

02:14:53.298 --> 02:14:55.175
[Croft] Hayes plays the decoy,

02:14:55.258 --> 02:14:59.637
and Pearce rockets past Leclerc
and up into second.

02:14:59.721 --> 02:15:05.185
And Leclerc's in danger from Sonny Hayes.
Round the outside, he's up into P3.

02:15:05.268 --> 02:15:06.644
[Brundle] Perfect teamwork.

02:15:06.728 --> 02:15:10.440
Hayes and Pearce working together,
it's like racing ballet.

02:15:11.024 --> 02:15:12.650
[Croft] It's a beautiful sight,

02:15:12.734 --> 02:15:16.696
but now their sights are set on
the race leader, Lewis Hamilton.

02:15:17.197 --> 02:15:18.656
Yeah! Remember me?

02:15:28.249 --> 02:15:30.001
Come on, boys. Send it!

02:15:57.195 --> 02:15:58.404
Why didn't they overtake?

02:15:58.488 --> 02:16:00.073
Lewis will defend
whichever car attacks first.

02:16:00.156 --> 02:16:03.493
-But they both can't wait.
-Someone has to sacrifice.

02:16:08.790 --> 02:16:09.791
[Croft] Two onto one,

02:16:09.874 --> 02:16:12.460
and all the pressure is on Lewis Hamilton

02:16:12.544 --> 02:16:15.380
as Apex work as a pack.

02:16:16.381 --> 02:16:17.423
Go win it, kid.

02:16:17.507 --> 02:16:19.259
Hayes makes the first move.

02:16:19.342 --> 02:16:22.262
-Hamilton defends. Pearce attacks.
-Yeah!

02:16:22.345 --> 02:16:24.848
-And Pearce has P1.
-[crowd cheering]

02:16:24.931 --> 02:16:26.224
-Yes!
-Yes, yes!

02:16:28.101 --> 02:16:30.228
[Croft] Toe-to-toe, wheel-to-wheel,

02:16:30.311 --> 02:16:33.898
this is epic racing
to finish off the season.

02:16:33.982 --> 02:16:36.651
And Sonny Hayes and Lewis Hamilton
aren't done yet.

02:16:36.734 --> 02:16:38.695
Hamilton, on Sonny Hayes.

02:16:38.778 --> 02:16:40.154
-There's contact!
-[crowd clamors]

02:16:40.237 --> 02:16:42.115
And through goes Hamilton.

02:16:44.993 --> 02:16:47.244
-Yes, yes!
-Come on!

02:16:47.327 --> 02:16:48.327
Yes!

02:16:48.996 --> 02:16:51.457
Guys, talk to me.
Where's Sonny? Can he finish?

02:16:51.540 --> 02:16:54.043
[crew member] One more lap, JP.
Hamilton never backs down.

02:16:54.127 --> 02:16:56.004
Can Sonny finish the race, man?

02:16:56.087 --> 02:16:58.381
[crew member] Yes, he's on track.
Just watch Lewis when he fights.

02:16:58.464 --> 02:17:01.175
You're P1. No more risks.

02:17:01.259 --> 02:17:02.343
No such thing.

02:17:03.636 --> 02:17:07.348
[Croft] The rookie holds his line.
He won't back down.

02:17:07.432 --> 02:17:11.019
He's here to fight
the seven-time world champion.

02:17:14.772 --> 02:17:15.982
That made contact.

02:17:16.065 --> 02:17:20.236
The leader and Lewis Hamilton
are out of this race.

02:17:20.320 --> 02:17:24.365
[Brundle] Despite yellow flags flying
at turn one, this race will continue.

02:17:24.449 --> 02:17:26.825
[Hugh] Sonny, push, push, push.
You're P1! You're P1!

02:17:27.368 --> 02:17:29.870
[Brundle] Apex GP has only one lap to go.

02:17:29.954 --> 02:17:33.040
The question is do they have the car?

02:17:33.625 --> 02:17:34.959
We have the driver.

02:17:38.796 --> 02:17:41.049
[muffled] Yeah! Go on, Sonny!

02:17:50.475 --> 02:17:52.184
[breathing heavily]

02:18:26.218 --> 02:18:27.218
What's happening?

02:18:27.887 --> 02:18:29.222
He's flying.

02:18:54.371 --> 02:18:56.290
[Hugh] Sonny, you did it! We won! We won!

02:18:56.374 --> 02:18:57.375
[crew cheering]

02:18:57.458 --> 02:18:59.043
Yeah!

02:19:03.840 --> 02:19:05.549
Yes!

02:19:10.305 --> 02:19:11.305
Yeah!

02:19:11.388 --> 02:19:13.099
[cheers]

02:19:15.894 --> 02:19:17.019
We won!

02:19:17.102 --> 02:19:19.981
-Yeah!
-[cheering continues]

02:19:22.901 --> 02:19:23.942
Yeah!

02:19:25.486 --> 02:19:26.779
We won!

02:19:28.656 --> 02:19:32.660
-We did it! Whoo!
-Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

02:19:33.995 --> 02:19:36.706
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

02:19:41.044 --> 02:19:43.504
-Come on! Yes!
-Yes!

02:19:54.807 --> 02:19:57.143
Means another three years
for Ruben, right?

02:19:58.853 --> 02:19:59.854
Yeah.

02:20:00.647 --> 02:20:02.524
I guess we'll check back about that deal.

02:20:05.485 --> 02:20:07.362
Presuming you're still on the board.

02:20:16.663 --> 02:20:20.458
[Croft] Breathtaking!
Breathless! Incredible!

02:20:20.542 --> 02:20:23.336
What an Abu Dhabi Grand Prix
this has been!

02:20:23.419 --> 02:20:25.421
What a victory as well!

02:20:25.505 --> 02:20:29.843
[Brundle] Absolutely. It's a race
for the ages. An absolute thriller.

02:20:29.926 --> 02:20:33.429
-And this man wins his first Grand Prix.
-Well done.

02:20:33.513 --> 02:20:35.223
-It's been 30 years in the making.
-Well done!

02:20:35.306 --> 02:20:38.601
And the team did a brilliant job
from the pit wall.

02:20:38.685 --> 02:20:42.105
-And of course we can't forget Pearce…
-Oi! What you smiling about?

02:20:42.188 --> 02:20:44.566
-…playing his part in this victory.
-[Sonny] You.

02:20:44.649 --> 02:20:47.026
I'm gonna win a million races.
You should at least have one.

02:20:47.110 --> 02:20:48.820
[Sonny laughing]

02:20:49.529 --> 02:20:50.947
We did it.

02:20:51.573 --> 02:20:52.949
[Sonny] Yeah, we did.

02:20:56.244 --> 02:20:57.871
[exclaims]

02:20:57.954 --> 02:20:58.955
Whoo!

02:21:01.708 --> 02:21:03.042
[sighs]

02:21:06.754 --> 02:21:07.839
[spectator] Sonny!

02:21:07.922 --> 02:21:09.340
No, no, no, no. Give it to him.

02:21:10.216 --> 02:21:11.718
No, no, no. Give it to him.

02:21:14.429 --> 02:21:16.764
Oh, my God. Thank you. Thank you.

02:21:21.519 --> 02:21:24.939
[cheering]

02:21:29.402 --> 02:21:31.237
Let's go!

02:21:32.322 --> 02:21:33.323
[mutters]

02:21:33.406 --> 02:21:35.033
[kisses] I love you.

02:21:42.999 --> 02:21:44.876
Yeah!

02:21:44.959 --> 02:21:47.045
Today we get to say…

02:21:47.128 --> 02:21:49.768
-"We are the best in the world!"
-"We are the best in the world!"

02:21:50.256 --> 02:21:52.550
[cheering]

02:22:12.654 --> 02:22:14.155
[cheering continues]

02:22:21.829 --> 02:22:23.831
[dramatic music playing]

02:22:28.753 --> 02:22:30.755
[breathing heavily]

02:22:41.474 --> 02:22:45.144
[breathing heavily]

02:22:56.739 --> 02:22:59.993
[cheering]

02:23:00.076 --> 02:23:01.077
Joshua.

02:23:01.160 --> 02:23:03.621
If you were ever to consider
to drive somewhere else,

02:23:03.705 --> 02:23:04.706
you know where to find me.

02:23:04.789 --> 02:23:08.418
Thanks, Toto, but I'm happy where I am.

02:23:09.127 --> 02:23:10.378
Congratulations.

02:23:12.839 --> 02:23:14.924
Yeah, baby! Let them wait!

02:23:15.008 --> 02:23:16.801
-Let them wait!
-[laughs]

02:23:16.885 --> 02:23:18.469
-[exclaims]
-[screams]

02:23:20.471 --> 02:23:21.639
[Ruben] The cup!

02:23:21.723 --> 02:23:24.517
Kate, you built a hell of a car.

02:23:24.601 --> 02:23:26.019
[chuckles]

02:23:28.396 --> 02:23:31.399
-[crowd exclaiming, chattering]
-[breathing heavily]

02:23:46.289 --> 02:23:47.290
[sighs]

02:24:06.309 --> 02:24:09.479
[panting]

02:24:18.238 --> 02:24:19.322
[chuckles]

02:24:20.031 --> 02:24:21.115
[chuckles]

02:24:28.164 --> 02:24:29.999
[Kate] Another race I don't know about?

02:24:31.751 --> 02:24:32.752
Somewhere.

02:24:34.420 --> 02:24:36.089
That beats this? [chuckles]

02:24:39.759 --> 02:24:40.760
Yeah.

02:24:44.264 --> 02:24:47.183
I wanted to say, "See you down the road,"

02:24:47.267 --> 02:24:49.769
but in a way that was more poetic.

02:24:52.605 --> 02:24:53.606
So…

02:24:55.984 --> 02:24:57.527
Can I see you down the road?

02:25:03.157 --> 02:25:04.158
Yes.

02:25:06.286 --> 02:25:07.537
[chuckles]

02:25:20.216 --> 02:25:21.968
Hang on to that until then.

02:25:24.137 --> 02:25:25.972
Okay. [chuckles]

02:25:29.350 --> 02:25:30.727
And drive fast.

02:25:30.810 --> 02:25:32.437
[Sonny chuckles]

02:25:40.737 --> 02:25:42.497
[Joshua] And where do you
think you're going?

02:25:43.156 --> 02:25:45.825
[chuckles] Don't worry about me.
Go celebrate.

02:25:45.909 --> 02:25:47.410
But you're off to where?

02:25:47.911 --> 02:25:50.538
You know, couple more dragons to slay.

02:25:51.039 --> 02:25:52.457
It's your team now.

02:25:55.251 --> 02:25:56.669
It was always my team.

02:25:56.753 --> 02:25:59.964
[both chuckle]

02:26:00.048 --> 02:26:01.216
I'll be watching.

02:26:02.592 --> 02:26:04.052
See you around, swan.

02:26:06.012 --> 02:26:08.848
[laughs]

02:26:08.932 --> 02:26:10.934
[dramatic music playing]

02:26:12.268 --> 02:26:13.269
[sighs]

02:26:47.220 --> 02:26:48.221
[music stops]

02:26:52.016 --> 02:26:54.269
["Hablando de Mí" playing on radio]

02:27:04.529 --> 02:27:06.573
[engine revving]

02:27:19.752 --> 02:27:20.753
Hello!

02:27:22.046 --> 02:27:23.089
[in Spanish] Buenas.

02:27:27.051 --> 02:27:28.531
I'm told you're looking for a driver.

02:27:29.804 --> 02:27:31.181
What's your name?

02:27:32.140 --> 02:27:33.391
Sonny Hayes.

02:27:37.854 --> 02:27:39.522
Have you ever driven Baja?

02:27:40.648 --> 02:27:41.649
Nope.

02:27:42.442 --> 02:27:43.651
We can't pay much.

02:27:44.235 --> 02:27:45.528
Not about the money.

02:27:50.283 --> 02:27:51.659
So what is it about?

02:27:53.369 --> 02:27:55.205
[chuckles]

02:27:55.288 --> 02:27:57.040
[rock music playing]

02:27:57.123 --> 02:27:59.751
♪ Hey ♪

02:27:59.834 --> 02:28:01.836
[engine revving]

02:28:04.923 --> 02:28:06.382
♪ Hey ♪

02:28:11.387 --> 02:28:13.890
♪ Flying through the city
With the speakers up loud ♪

02:28:13.973 --> 02:28:16.476
♪ Speeding by with the top down ♪

02:28:17.185 --> 02:28:19.771
♪ Fast lane living
Till they put me in the ground ♪

02:28:19.854 --> 02:28:21.898
♪ And I don't wanna stop now ♪

02:28:22.649 --> 02:28:25.318
♪ Pull away, wind blowing
Now I'm cruising ♪

02:28:25.401 --> 02:28:28.571
♪ Put the past in the past
A new day is coming ♪

02:28:28.655 --> 02:28:31.491
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can ride ♪

02:28:31.574 --> 02:28:34.494
♪ Four wheels, you and I
Gotta get out of here ♪

02:28:34.577 --> 02:28:38.456
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:28:40.250 --> 02:28:43.294
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can fly ♪

02:28:43.378 --> 02:28:46.130
♪ Out of this burning fire
Just take me anywhere ♪

02:28:46.214 --> 02:28:49.968
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:28:50.051 --> 02:28:52.220
♪ Pedal down and drive ♪

02:28:54.013 --> 02:28:55.348
♪ Drive ♪

02:28:55.890 --> 02:28:57.600
♪ Pedal down and ♪

02:28:57.684 --> 02:29:01.062
♪ Drive ♪

02:29:02.772 --> 02:29:06.526
♪ Just drive ♪

02:29:09.237 --> 02:29:11.823
♪ Out of the city
Now we're switching four lanes ♪

02:29:11.906 --> 02:29:14.117
♪ Got our eyes on a fresh start ♪

02:29:14.868 --> 02:29:17.620
♪ The world as we knew it
That was caught up in flames ♪

02:29:17.704 --> 02:29:19.789
♪ Get ready for the next part ♪

02:29:20.331 --> 02:29:23.251
♪ You know I'm good
If I'm back in the gutter ♪

02:29:23.334 --> 02:29:26.504
♪ 'Cause this life
It was never about the money ♪

02:29:26.588 --> 02:29:29.424
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can ride ♪

02:29:29.507 --> 02:29:32.427
♪ Four wheels, you and I
Gotta get out of here ♪

02:29:32.510 --> 02:29:36.222
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

02:29:38.099 --> 02:29:40.935
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, we can fly ♪

02:29:41.019 --> 02:29:43.938
♪ Out of this, good and far
Just take me anywhere ♪

02:29:44.022 --> 02:29:47.901
♪ Ha-la-lay-la, my savior ♪

